{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779187312298,"sessionID":"ses_1c02c8023ffenJEyiMDWsaqbGv","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_02_REgLOtgMWMQnqr8fbsSt3782","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/best-practices.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/best-practices.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Backend Best Practices\n2: \n3: ## CRITICAL RULES (MANDATORY)\n4: \n5: ### Rule 1: Message Punctuation Convention (MANDATORY)\n6: \n7: All user-facing messages in the backend MUST follow these punctuation rules:\n8: \n9: **Success messages** must be meaningful and end with a period `.`:\n10: ```typescript\n11: // ✅ CORRECT: Success messages end with \".\"\n12: return new SuccessResponseDto(data, 'Project created successfully.');\n13: return new ResponsePayloadDto({ message: 'Login successful.' });\n14: ```\n15: \n16: ```typescript\n17: // ❌ WRONG: Missing period, or too vague\n18: return new SuccessResponseDto(data, 'Success');\n19: return new SuccessResponseDto(data, 'Project created successfully');\n20: ```\n21: \n22: **Error messages** must be meaningful and end with an exclamation mark `!`:\n23: ```typescript\n24: // ✅ CORRECT: Error messages end with \"!\" and are descriptive\n25: throw new NotFoundException(`Project with ID ${id} not found!`);\n26: throw new ForbiddenException('You do not have permission to access this resource!');\n27: throw new UnauthorizedException('The access ID or password you entered is incorrect!');\n28: ```\n29: \n30: ```typescript\n31: // ❌ WRONG: Missing \"!\", or too vague\n32: throw new NotFoundException('Not found');\n33: throw new ForbiddenException('Access denied');\n34: throw new UnauthorizedException('Invalid credentials');\n35: ```\n36: \n37: **Avoid vague messages** — be specific about what went wrong or succeeded:\n38: | ❌ Vague | ✅ Meaningful |\n39: |----------|--------------|\n40: | `'Access denied'` | `'You do not have permission to access this resource!'` |\n41: | `'Invalid token'` | `'The authentication token is invalid or malformed!'` |\n42: | `'Success'` | `'Project created successfully.'` |\n43: | `'Not found'` | `'Project with ID ${id} not found!'` |\n44: \n45: ### Rule 1b: Multi-Language i18n (MANDATORY)\n46: \n47: All messages use `nestjs-i18n` for multi-language support. The `I18nHelper.t()` static utility auto-resolves the user's language from `Accept-Language` header or `?lang=` query parameter.\n48: \n49: **When adding new messages:**\n50: 1. Add the key to `backend/src/i18n/en/translation.json` (English)\n51: 2. Add the key to `backend/src/i18n/ko/translation.json` (Korean)\n52: 3. Use via `I18nHelper.t('domain.key', { param: value })`\n53: \n54: ```typescript\n55: // ✅ CORRECT: Use I18nHelper.t() — auto-resolves language\n56: throw new NotFoundException(I18nHelper.t('projects.notFound', { id }));\n57: return new SuccessResponseDto(data, I18nHelper.t('projects.created'));\n58: ```\n59: \n60: ```typescript\n61: // ❌ WRONG: Hardcoded strings bypass multi-language support\n62: throw new NotFoundException(`Project with ID ${id} not found!`);\n63: return new SuccessResponseDto(data, 'Project created successfully.');\n64: ```\n65: \n66: ### Rule 2: Check Existing APIs Before Creating New Ones\n67: \n68: **Before creating any new API endpoint, you MUST search for existing endpoints.**\n69: \n70: ```bash\n71: # Search for existing endpoints\n72: grep -r \"@Get\\|@Post\\|@Put\\|@Patch\\|@Delete\" backend/src/modules/ --include=\"*.controller.ts\"\n73: ```\n74: \n75: | Frontend Need | Check First |\n76: |---------------|-------------|\n77: | Get user profile | `GET /users/:id` or `GET /users/me` |\n78: | Update user | `PATCH /users/:id` |\n79: | Get list with filters | Existing `GET /` with query params |\n80: \n81: **Only create new endpoint when**:\n82: - Operation is fundamentally different\n83: - Business logic is completely distinct\n84: - Access control requirements differ\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## NestJS Coding Standards\n89: \n90: ### General Principles\n91: \n92: 1. **Use TypeScript Strict Mode**: Enable strict type checking\n93: 2. **Follow Single Responsibility Principle**: Each class should have one clear purpose\n94: 3. **Dependency Injection**: Use constructor injection for all dependencies\n95: 4. **Immutability**: Prefer const over let, avoid mutations when possible\n96: 5. **Async/Await**: Always use async/await, never promise chains\n97: \n98: ### Naming Conventions\n99: \n100: - **Files**: kebab-case (e.g., `user.controller.ts`, `auth.service.ts`)\n101: - **Classes**: PascalCase (e.g., `UserController`, `AuthService`)\n102: - **Variables/Functions**: camelCase (e.g., `findUser`, `isActive`)\n103: - **Constants**: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (e.g., `MAX_RETRIES`, `API_URL`)\n104: - **Interfaces**: PascalCase with 'I' prefix (e.g., `IJwtPayload`, `IUser`)\n105: - **DTOs**: PascalCase with suffix (e.g., `CreateUserDto`, `UpdatePostDto`)\n106: - **Entities**: PascalCase (e.g., `User`, `Post`)\n107: \n108: ### Controller Best Practices\n109: \n110: **MANDATORY: Controllers MUST extend BaseController. Writing a controller without extending BaseController is PROHIBITED.**\n111: \n112: ```typescript\n113: // ✅ GOOD: Extends BaseController, uses decorators, no try/catch\n114: @ApiTags('Users')\n115: @Controller('users')\n116: export class UserController extends BaseController<\n117:     User,\n118:     CreateUserDto,\n119:     UpdateUserDto\n120: > {\n121:     constructor(private readonly userService: UserService) {\n122:         super(userService);\n123:     }\n124: \n125:     // Custom endpoint beyond CRUD — override only when needed\n126:     @Post(':id/reset-password')\n127:     @Roles('admin')\n128:     async resetPassword(\n129:         @Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string,\n130:         @Body() dto: ResetPasswordDto,\n131:     ): Promise<void> {\n132:         await this.userService.resetPassword(id, dto);\n133:     }\n134: }\n135: \n136: // ❌ PROHIBITED: No base class — will FAIL backend gate check\n137: export class UserController {\n138:     async getUser(req, res) {\n139:         try {\n140:             const user = await this.userService.findById(req.params.id);\n141:             res.json(user);\n142:         } catch (error) {\n143:             res.status(500).json({ error: error.message });\n144:         }\n145:     }\n146: }\n147: ```\n148: \n149: ### Service Best Practices\n150: \n151: **MANDATORY: Services MUST extend BaseService. Services MUST inject custom repository classes — using `@InjectRepository(Entity)` directly in services is PROHIBITED.**\n152: \n153: ```typescript\n154: // ✅ GOOD: Extends BaseService, injects custom repository\n155: @Injectable()\n156: export class UserService extends BaseService<User> {\n157:     constructor(\n158:         protected readonly repository: UserRepository,  // ✅ Custom repository\n159:         private readonly mailService: MailService,\n160:     ) {\n161:         super(repository, 'User');\n162:     }\n163: \n164:     async findByEmail(email: string): Promise<User> {\n165:         const user = await this.repository.findOne({ where: { email } });\n166: \n167:         if (!user) {\n168:             throw new NotFoundException(`User with email ${email} not found`);\n169:         }\n170: \n171:         return user;\n172:     }\n173: \n174:     async createUser(dto: CreateUserDto): Promise<User> {\n175:         const existing = await this.repository.findOne({\n176:             where: { email: dto.email },\n177:         });\n178: \n179:         if (existing) {\n180:             throw new ConflictException('Email already exists');\n181:         }\n182: \n183:         const user = await this.repository.save(dto);\n184:         await this.mailService.sendWelcomeEmail(user.email);\n185: \n186:         return user;\n187:     }\n188: }\n189: \n190: // ❌ PROHIBITED: Direct @InjectRepository — will FAIL backend gate check\n191: @Injectable()\n192: export class UserService {\n193:     constructor(\n194:         @InjectRepository(User)\n195:         private readonly userRepository: Repository<User>,  // ❌ WRONG\n196:     ) {}\n197: }\n198: \n199: // ❌ PROHIBITED: No base class\n200: export class UserService {\n201:     async getUser(id) {\n202:         return User.findOne(id); // No validation, no error handling\n203:     }\n204: }\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ### DTO Best Practices\n208: \n209: ```typescript\n210: // GOOD: class-validator decorators, Swagger docs, proper typing\n211: export class CreateUserDto {\n212:     @ApiProperty({ example: 'user@example.com' })\n213:     @IsEmail()\n214:     @IsNotEmpty()\n215:     email: string;\n216: \n217:     @ApiProperty({ example: 'Password@123' })\n218:     @IsString()\n219:     @MinLength(8)\n220:     @Matches(/^(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*\\d)/, {\n221:         message: 'Password must contain uppercase, lowercase, and number',\n222:     })\n223:     password: string;\n224: \n225:     @ApiPropertyOptional({ example: 'John' })\n226:     @IsString()\n227:     @IsOptional()\n228:     firstName?: string;\n229: }\n230: \n231: // BAD: No validation, plain interface\n232: interface CreateUserDto {\n233:     email: string;\n234:     password: string;\n235: }\n236: ```\n237: \n238: ### Entity Best Practices\n239: \n240: ```typescript\n241: // GOOD: Extends BaseEntity, proper decorators, relationships\n242: @Entity('users')\n243: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n244:     @Column({ unique: true })\n245:     @Index()\n246:     email: string;\n247: \n248:     @Column()\n249:     password: string;\n250: \n251:     @Column({ nullable: true })\n252:     firstName: string;\n253: \n254:     @Column({ nullable: true })\n255:     lastName: string;\n256: \n257:     @Column({ type: 'enum', enum: UserRole, default: UserRole.USER })\n258:     role: UserRole;\n259: \n260:     @OneToMany(() => Post, (post) => post.author)\n261:     posts: Post[];\n262: \n263:     @BeforeInsert()\n264:     async hashPassword() {\n265:         this.password = await bcrypt.hash(this.password, 10);\n266:     }\n267: }\n268: \n269: // BAD: No base class, missing indexes, business logic in entity\n270: @Entity()\n271: export class User {\n272:     @PrimaryGeneratedColumn()\n273:     id: number; // Should be UUID\n274: \n275:     @Column()\n276:     email: string; // Should have unique constraint\n277: \n278:     async validatePassword(password: string) {\n279:         // Business logic should be in service\n280:         return bcrypt.compare(password, this.password);\n281:     }\n282: }\n283: ```\n284: \n285: ## Error Handling Patterns\n286: \n287: ### DO\n288: \n289: ```typescript\n290: // Throw HTTP exceptions from services\n291: throw new NotFoundException('User not found');\n292: throw new ConflictException('Email already exists');\n293: throw new BadRequestException('Invalid input');\n294: \n295: // Let exception filters handle errors in controllers\n296: @Get(':id')\n297: async findOne(@Param('id') id: string) {\n298:     return await this.service.findById(id); // No try/catch\n299: }\n300: \n301: // Add Sentry context for unexpected errors\n302: Sentry.withScope((scope) => {\n303:     scope.setContext('user', { id, email });\n304:     Sentry.captureException(error);\n305: });\n306: ```\n307: \n308: ### DON'T\n309: \n310: ```typescript\n311: // Don't use try/catch in controllers\n312: @Get(':id')\n313: async findOne(@Param('id') id: string) {\n314:     try {\n315:         return await this.service.findById(id);\n316:     } catch (error) {\n317:         throw error; // Exception filter will handle it\n318:     }\n319: }\n320: \n321: // Don't swallow errors\n322: catch (error) {\n323:     console.error(error); // Lost error\n324:     return null;\n325: }\n326: \n327: // Don't use generic error messages\n328: throw new Error('Error occurred'); // Too generic\n329: ```\n330: \n331: ## Database Patterns\n332: \n333: **MANDATORY: `createQueryBuilder()` MUST only be used in repository files — using it in services is PROHIBITED. Services access data through custom repository methods.**\n334: \n335: ### DO\n336: \n337: ```typescript\n338: // ✅ GOOD: createQueryBuilder in REPOSITORY layer\n339: // user.repository.ts\n340: @Injectable()\n341: export class UserRepository extends BaseRepository<User> {\n342:     async findAdminsWithPosts(): Promise<User[]> {\n343:         return this.repository\n344:             .createQueryBuilder('user')\n345:             .leftJoinAndSelect('user.posts', 'posts')\n346:             .where('user.role = :role', { role: UserRole.ADMIN })\n347:             .getMany();\n348:     }\n349: }\n350: \n351: // ✅ GOOD: Service calls repository method\n352: // user.service.ts\n353: async getAdmins(): Promise<User[]> {\n354:     return this.repository.findAdminsWithPosts();\n355: }\n356: \n357: // ✅ GOOD: Use transactions for multi-step operations\n358: const queryRunner = this.dataSource.createQueryRunner();\n359: await queryRunner.connect();\n360: await queryRunner.startTransaction();\n361: \n362: try {\n363:     await queryRunner.manager.save(user);\n364:     await queryRunner.manager.save(profile);\n365:     await queryRunner.commitTransaction();\n366: } catch (error) {\n367:     await queryRunner.rollbackTransaction();\n368:     throw error;\n369: } finally {\n370:     await queryRunner.release();\n371: }\n372: ```\n373: \n374: ### DON'T\n375: \n376: ```typescript\n377: // ❌ PROHIBITED: createQueryBuilder in SERVICE — will FAIL backend gate check\n378: // user.service.ts\n379: async getAdmins() {\n380:     return this.repository.createQueryBuilder('user')\n381:         .where('user.role = :role', { role: 'admin' })\n382:         .getMany();\n383: }\n384: \n385: // ❌ Don't use raw SQL\n386: const users = await this.dataSource.query('SELECT * FROM users');\n387: \n388: // ❌ Don't hard delete (use soft delete)\n389: await this.repository.delete(id); // Use remove() instead\n390: \n391: // ❌ Don't forget to release query runners\n392: const queryRunner = this.dataSource.createQueryRunner();\n393: await queryRunner.startTransaction();\n394: // ... operations\n395: await queryRunner.commitTransaction();\n396: // Missing: await queryRunner.release();\n397: ```\n398: \n399: ## Security Best Practices\n400: \n401: 1. **Never commit secrets**: Use environment variables\n402: 2. **Hash passwords**: Use bcrypt before storing\n403: 3. **Validate all inputs**: Use class-validator decorators\n404: 4. **Use UUIDs**: Never expose auto-increment IDs\n405: 5. **Implement rate limiting**: Protect against brute force\n406: 6. **Enable CORS properly**: Only allow trusted origins\n407: 7. **Use HTTPS**: In production environments\n408: 8. **Sanitize user input**: Prevent XSS and SQL injection\n409: \n410: ## Performance Best Practices\n411: \n412: 1. **Use pagination**: For all list endpoints\n413: 2. **Index database columns**: For frequently queried fields\n414: 3. **Eager vs lazy loading**: Choose based on use case\n415: 4. **Cache frequently accessed data**: Use Redis when appropriate\n416: 5. **Optimize database queries**: Avoid N+1 queries\n417: 6. **Use compression**: Enable gzip compression\n418: 7. **Monitor slow queries**: Set up database query logging\n419: \n420: ## Testing Best Practices\n421: \n422: 1. **Write unit tests for services**: Test business logic\n423: 2. **Write e2e tests for controllers**: Test API endpoints\n424: 3. **Mock external dependencies**: Don't call real APIs in tests\n425: 4. **Use test database**: Never test against production\n426: 5. **Clean up after tests**: Reset database state\n427: 6. **Test edge cases**: Not just happy paths\n428: 7. **Achieve good coverage**: Aim for >80% coverage\n429: \n430: ## curl API Testing Best Practices\n431: \n432: ### Token Authentication with curl\n433: \n434: **CRITICAL: Always use single quotes for curl commands to prevent shell variable expansion issues!**\n435: \n436: #### Correct Format (Single Quotes)\n437: \n438: ```bash\n439: # GET request\n440: curl -s -X GET 'http://localhost:3000/users' \\\n441:   -H 'Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...' \\\n442:   | python3 -m json.tool\n443: \n444: # POST request with JSON body\n445: curl -s -X POST 'http://localhost:3000/posts' \\\n446:   -H 'Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...' \\\n447:   -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n448:   -d '{\"title\":\"My Post\",\"content\":\"Content here...\",\"published\":true}' \\\n449:   | python3 -m json.tool\n450: ```\n451: \n452: #### Why Shell Variables Fail\n453: \n454: Using shell variables with `$TOKEN` often fails due to shell expansion issues:\n455: \n456: ```bash\n457: # THIS OFTEN FAILS - token becomes empty!\n458: TOKEN=\"eyJhbGci...\"\n459: curl -X GET \"http://localhost:3000/users\" -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\"\n460: # Result: Authorization: Bearer  (empty!)\n461: \n462: # WORKAROUND if you must use variables - use && in same line:\n463: TOKEN=\"eyJhbGci...\" && curl -s -X GET \"http://localhost:3000/users\" -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\"\n464: ```\n465: \n466: ### Getting a Valid Token\n467: \n468: **Step 1: Login to get a token**\n469: \n470: ```bash\n471: curl -s -X POST 'http://localhost:3000/auth/login' \\\n472:   -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n473:   -d '{\"email\": \"admin@example.com\", \"password\": \"Password123!\"}' | python3 -m json.tool\n474: ```\n475: \n476: **Note**: Login uses `email` and `password`.\n477: \n478: ### Generating Test Tokens\n479: \n480: Use the helper script:\n481: \n482: ```bash\n483: cd backend\n484: node test/generate-test-token.js\n485: ```\n486: \n487: Or manually:\n488: \n489: ```javascript\n490: const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');\n491: const JWT_SECRET = 'your-secret-key';  // from .env AUTH_JWT_SECRET\n492: \n493: const token = jwt.sign({\n494:   id: 'USER_UUID_FROM_DB',\n495:   email: 'user@example.com',\n496:   role: 2,  // 1=ADMIN, 2=USER, 3=MODERATOR\n497:   fullName: 'User Name',\n498: }, JWT_SECRET, { expiresIn: '24h' });\n499: \n500: console.log(token);\n501: ```\n502: \n503: ### User Roles Reference\n504: \n505: | Role | Value | Description |\n506: |------|-------|-------------|\n507: | ADMIN | 1 | Full system access |\n508: | USER | 2 | Standard user (default) |\n509: | MODERATOR | 3 | Content moderation |\n510: \n511: **Usage**: Use `@Roles(RolesEnum.ADMIN)` decorator to restrict access.\n512: \n513: ### Common Token Errors\n514: \n515: | Error | Cause | Solution |\n516: |-------|-------|----------|\n517: | `Authorization: Bearer ` (empty) | Shell variable expansion failed | Use single quotes with inline token |\n518: | `Invalid or missing token` | Token expired or malformed | Get fresh token via login |\n519: | `Access denied. Required roles: ADMIN` | Wrong role in token | Login with correct user role |\n520: | `property username should not exist` | Login expects `email` | Use `{\"email\": \"user@example.com\", ...}` |\n521: \n522: ### Complete curl Examples\n523: \n524: ```bash\n525: # Create post (authenticated)\n526: curl -s -X POST 'http://localhost:3000/posts' \\\n527:   -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN' \\\n528:   -H 'Content-Type: application/json' \\\n529:   -d '{\"title\":\"My Post\",\"content\":\"Post content here...\",\"published\":true}' \\\n530:   | python3 -m json.tool\n531: \n532: # Get all users (authenticated)\n533: curl -s -X GET 'http://localhost:3000/users' \\\n534:   -H 'Authorization: Bearer YOUR_TOKEN' \\\n535:   | python3 -m json.tool\n536: \n537: # Get published posts (public)\n538: curl -s -X GET 'http://localhost:3000/posts/published' \\\n539:   | python3 -m json.tool\n540: ```\n541: \n542: ## Redis Caching Best Practices\n543: \n544: ### What to Cache\n545: \n546: | Data Type | TTL | Example |\n547: |-----------|-----|---------|\n548: | Static catalogs | `'catalog'` (1h) | Items, products, categories |\n549: | Entity lists | `'list'` (30m) | Users, assignments, meetings |\n550: | Computed stats | `'stats'` (15m) | Dashboard, aggregates |\n551: | User-specific | `'default'` (5m) | Profiles, preferences |\n552: | Real-time | NEVER | Notifications, live status |\n553: \n554: ### DO\n555: \n556: ```typescript\n557: // Cache GET endpoints with appropriate TTL\n558: @Get()\n559: @Cacheable({ key: 'items:all', ttl: 'catalog' })\n560: async findAll() { ... }\n561: \n562: // Invalidate on mutations\n563: @Post()\n564: @CacheInvalidate({ patterns: ['items:*'] })\n565: async create(@Body() dto: CreateDto) { ... }\n566: \n567: // Use userAware for user-specific data\n568: @Cacheable({ key: 'profile', ttl: 'default', userAware: true })\n569: ```\n570: \n571: ### DON'T\n572: \n573: ```typescript\n574: // Don't cache mutation endpoints\n575: @Post()\n576: @Cacheable({ key: 'result' })  // WRONG!\n577: async create() { ... }\n578: \n579: // Don't forget to invalidate related caches\n580: @Patch(':id')\n581: // Missing @CacheInvalidate!\n582: async update() { ... }\n583: \n584: // Don't use overly long TTLs for dynamic data\n585: @Cacheable({ key: 'notifications', ttl: 3600 })  // Too long!\n586: ```\n587: \n588: See [workflow-implement-redis-caching.md](workflow-implement-redis-caching.md) for complete documentation.\n589: \n590: ---\n591: \n592: ## Socket.IO (WebSocket) Best Practices\n593: \n594: ### Backend Gateway Pattern\n595: \n596: ```typescript\n597: // GOOD: Proper gateway with authentication and validation\n598: @WebSocketGateway({\n599:     namespace: '/chat',\n600:     cors: {\n601:         origin: '*',\n602:         credentials: true,\n603:     },\n604: })\n605: @UseFilters(WsExceptionFilter)\n606: @UsePipes(new ValidationPipe({ transform: true, whitelist: true }))\n607: export class ChatGateway implements OnGatewayConnection, OnGatewayDisconnect {\n608:     @WebSocketServer()\n609:     server: Server;\n610: \n611:     private connectedUsers: Map<string, Set<string>> = new Map(); // userId -> socketIds\n612: \n613:     async handleConnection(client: AuthenticatedSocket) {\n614:         try {\n615:             const token = this.extractTokenFromCookie(client);\n616:             const payload = await this.jwtService.verifyAsync(token);\n617:             client.userId = payload.sub || payload.id;\n618: \n619:             // Track user connections (supports multi-device)\n620:             if (!this.connectedUsers.has(client.userId)) {\n621:                 this.connectedUsers.set(client.userId, new Set());\n622:             }\n623:             this.connectedUsers.get(client.userId).add(client.id);\n624:         } catch (error) {\n625:             client.disconnect();\n626:         }\n627:     }\n628: \n629:     @SubscribeMessage('room:join')\n630:     async handleJoinRoom(\n631:         @ConnectedSocket() client: AuthenticatedSocket,\n632:         @MessageBody() data: WsJoinRoomDto,\n633:     ) {\n634:         await this.verifyAccess(data.roomId, client.userId);\n635:         await client.join(`room:${data.roomId}`);\n636:         return { event: 'room:joined', data: { success: true } };\n637:     }\n638: }\n639: ```\n640: \n641: ### Socket Authentication via Cookies\n642: \n643: ```typescript\n644: // Backend: Extract token from HTTP-only cookie\n645: private extractToken(client: Socket): string | null {\n646:     const cookieHeader = client.handshake.headers.cookie;\n647:     if (cookieHeader) {\n648:         const cookies = this.parseCookies(cookieHeader);\n649:         return cookies['NestjsStartKit'] || null;\n650:     }\n651:     return null;\n652: }\n653: ```\n654: \n655: ### Common Socket Event Naming\n656: \n657: | Event | Direction | Purpose |\n658: |-------|-----------|---------|\n659: | `room:join` | Client -> Server | Join a room |\n660: | `room:leave` | Client -> Server | Leave a room |\n661: | `message:send` | Client -> Server | Send a message |\n662: | `message:new` | Server -> Client | New message broadcast |\n663: | `message:typing` | Bidirectional | Typing indicator |\n664: | `message:read` | Bidirectional | Read receipt |\n665: | `user:online` | Server -> Client | Online status change |\n666: \n667: ---\n668: \n669: ## MANDATORY Rules (from Base Architecture)\n670: \n671: ### UnifiedConfig — No Direct `process.env`\n672: \n673: All environment variable access MUST go through `UnifiedConfig`:\n674: \n675: ```typescript\n676: // BAD: Direct process.env access\n677: const secret = process.env.JWT_SECRET;\n678: \n679: // GOOD: UnifiedConfig\n680: import { UnifiedConfig } from '@/config/unified-config';\n681: const secret = UnifiedConfig.jwt.secret;\n682: ```\n683: \n684: - NEVER use `process.env` directly in services, controllers, or utilities\n685: - All config values defined in `UnifiedConfig` class with validation\n686: - Missing required values MUST throw on startup (not fallback to defaults)\n687: \n688: ### Enum Centralization\n689: \n690: ALL constrained values (status, role, type) MUST be TypeScript enums:\n691: \n692: ```typescript\n693: // Location: backend/src/shared/enums/user-status.enum.ts\n694: export enum UserStatusEnum {\n695:   ACTIVE = 'active',\n696:   SUSPENDED = 'suspended',\n697: }\n698: ```\n699: \n700: - Create in `backend/src/shared/enums/` with `Enum` suffix\n701: - Export from barrel `backend/src/shared/enums/index.ts`\n702: - Reference in entity: `@Column({ type: 'enum', enum: UserStatusEnum })`\n703: - After creating/modifying enums, run `/sync-enums` to sync to frontend\n704: - No hardcoded string literals for constrained values\n705: \n706: ### Pagination Defaults\n707: \n708: - Default `limit`: 20\n709: - Maximum `limit`: 100\n710: - All list endpoints MUST support pagination\n711: - Response shape: `{ data: T[], total: number, totalPages: number, page: number, limit: number }`\n712: \n713: ### Rate Limiting\n714: \n715: - Public endpoints (login, register, forgot-password) MUST have rate limiting\n716: - Use `@nestjs/throttler` or custom guard\n717: - Default: 10 requests per 60 seconds for auth endpoints\n718: \n719: ### File Size Constraints\n720: \n721: | Layer | Max Lines | Action at Limit |\n722: |-------|-----------|-----------------|\n723: | Controller | 200 | Split into sub-controllers |\n724: | Service | 300 | Extract helper services |\n725: | Repository | 200 | Extract query builders |\n726: \n727: ### Sentry Error Context\n728: \n729: When throwing exceptions in services, enrich with Sentry context:\n730: \n731: ```typescript\n732: import * as Sentry from '@sentry/node';\n733: \n734: // Add context before throwing\n735: Sentry.setContext('operation', { userId, action: 'createOrder' });\n736: throw new ConflictException(I18nHelper.t('order.alreadyExists'));\n737: ```\n\n(End of file - total 737 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Backend Best Practices\n\n## CRITICAL RULES (MANDATORY)\n\n### Rule 1: Message Punctuation Convention (MANDATORY)\n\nAll user-facing messages in the backend MUST follow these punctuation rules:\n\n**Success messages** must be meaningful and end with a period `.`:\n```typescript\n// ✅ CORRECT: Success messages end with \".\"\nreturn new SuccessResponseDto(data, 'Project created successfully.');\nreturn new ResponsePayloadDto({ message: 'Login successful.' });\n```\n\n```typescript\n// ❌ WRONG: Missing period, or too vague\nreturn new SuccessResponseDto(data, 'Success');\nreturn new SuccessResponseDto(data, 'Project created successfully');\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/nestjs/guides/best-practices.md","time":{"start":1779187312014,"end":1779187312296}},"id":"prt_e3fd3dfd30010aN5yRcpm5n3ro","sessionID":"ses_1c02c8023ffenJEyiMDWsaqbGv","messageID":"msg_e3fd384c2001epneAUIDsTOGpZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779187314093,"sessionID":"ses_1c02c8023ffenJEyiMDWsaqbGv","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_03_8Pbahnh1V0RPMhSrjbzc2551","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/routing-and-controllers.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/routing-and-controllers.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Routing and Controllers - NestJS Best Practices\n2: \n3: Complete guide to NestJS controllers with BaseController pattern and decorators.\n4: \n5: ## Table of Contents\n6: \n7: - [NestJS Controllers Overview](#nestjs-controllers-overview)\n8: - [BaseController Pattern](#basecontroller-pattern)\n9: - [Route Decorators](#route-decorators)\n10: - [Custom Decorators](#custom-decorators)\n11: - [Good Examples](#good-examples)\n12: - [Anti-Patterns](#anti-patterns)\n13: - [Swagger Documentation](#swagger-documentation)\n14: - [Override Pattern](#override-pattern)\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## NestJS Controllers Overview\n19: \n20: ### The Golden Rule\n21: \n22: **Controllers should ONLY:**\n23: \n24: - ✅ Define routes with decorators (@Get, @Post, etc.)\n25: - ✅ Extract request data (@Param, @Body, @Query)\n26: - ✅ Delegate to services\n27: - ✅ Return responses (wrapped automatically)\n28: \n29: **Controllers should NEVER:**\n30: \n31: - ❌ Contain business logic\n32: - ❌ Access database directly (use services)\n33: - ❌ Handle complex validations (DTOs handle this)\n34: - ❌ Format responses manually (TransformInterceptor does this)\n35: \n36: ### Clean Controller Pattern\n37: \n38: ```typescript\n39: // src/modules/users/user.controller.ts\n40: import {\n41:     Controller,\n42:     Get,\n43:     Post,\n44:     Body,\n45:     Param,\n46:     ParseUUIDPipe,\n47: } from '@nestjs/common';\n48: import { ApiTags } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n49: import { BaseController } from 'src/core/base';\n50: import { ApiSwagger } from 'src/core/decorators';\n51: import { UserService } from './user.service';\n52: import { User } from './user.entity';\n53: import { CreateUserDto, UpdateUserDto } from './dtos';\n54: \n55: @ApiTags('Users')\n56: @Controller('users')\n57: export class UserController extends BaseController<\n58:     User,\n59:     CreateUserDto,\n60:     UpdateUserDto\n61: > {\n62:     constructor(private readonly userService: UserService) {\n63:         super(userService);\n64:     }\n65: \n66:     // All CRUD operations inherited automatically!\n67:     // - POST   /users\n68:     // - GET    /users\n69:     // - GET    /users/:id\n70:     // - PATCH  /users/:id\n71:     // - DELETE /users/:id\n72: }\n73: ```\n74: \n75: **Key Points:**\n76: \n77: - Extends BaseController for automatic CRUD\n78: - Decorator-based routing (@Get, @Post, etc.)\n79: - Type-safe with generics\n80: - Clean, readable, maintainable\n81: - All endpoints visible at a glance\n82: \n83: ---\n84: \n85: ## BaseController Pattern\n86: \n87: ### Why BaseController?\n88: \n89: **Benefits:**\n90: \n91: - ✅ **90% less code** - Full CRUD automatically\n92: - ✅ **Consistent responses** - All wrapped in ResponsePayloadDto\n93: - ✅ **Automatic validation** - UUID validation on :id routes\n94: - ✅ **Swagger docs** - Auto-generated with @ApiSwagger\n95: - ✅ **Error handling** - Inherited from base\n96: - ✅ **Pagination support** - Built-in for GET /\n97: - ✅ **Type-safe** - Generic types throughout\n98: \n99: ### Inherited CRUD Operations\n100: \n101: When you extend BaseController, you automatically get:\n102: \n103: ```typescript\n104: @Post()\n105: @HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)\n106: @ApiSwagger({ resourceName: 'Resource', operation: 'create', successStatus: 201 })\n107: async create(@Body() createDto: CreateDto): Promise<CreatedResponseDto<T>>\n108: \n109: @Get()\n110: @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n111: @ApiSwagger({ resourceName: 'Resources', operation: 'getAll', isArray: true, withPagination: true })\n112: async findAll(@Query() paginationDto: PaginationDto): Promise<PaginatedResponseDto<T>>\n113: \n114: @Get(':id')\n115: @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n116: @ApiSwagger({ resourceName: 'Resource', operation: 'getOne' })\n117: async findOne(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string): Promise<SuccessResponseDto<T>>\n118: \n119: @Patch(':id')\n120: @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n121: @ApiSwagger({ resourceName: 'Resource', operation: 'update' })\n122: async update(\n123:     @Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string,\n124:     @Body() updateDto: UpdateDto\n125: ): Promise<UpdatedResponseDto<T>>\n126: \n127: @Delete(':id')\n128: @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n129: @ApiSwagger({ resourceName: 'Resource', operation: 'delete' })\n130: async remove(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string): Promise<DeletedResponseDto>\n131: ```\n132: \n133: ### Response Format\n134: \n135: All responses are automatically wrapped by TransformInterceptor:\n136: \n137: ```typescript\n138: {\n139:     \"success\": true,\n140:     \"statusCode\": 200,\n141:     \"message\": \"User retrieved successfully\",\n142:     \"data\": {\n143:         \"id\": \"uuid-here\",\n144:         \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n145:         \"name\": \"John Doe\",\n146:         \"createdAt\": \"2024-01-01T12:00:00.000Z\",\n147:         \"updatedAt\": \"2024-01-01T12:00:00.000Z\"\n148:     },\n149:     \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-01T12:00:00.000Z\",\n150:     \"path\": \"/api/users/uuid-here\"\n151: }\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ---\n155: \n156: ## Route Decorators\n157: \n158: ### HTTP Method Decorators\n159: \n160: ```typescript\n161: import {\n162:     Get,\n163:     Post,\n164:     Put,\n165:     Patch,\n166:     Delete,\n167:     HttpCode,\n168:     HttpStatus,\n169: } from '@nestjs/common';\n170: \n171: @Controller('users')\n172: export class UserController {\n173:     @Get() // GET /users\n174:     @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK) // 200\n175:     findAll() {}\n176: \n177:     @Get(':id') // GET /users/:id\n178:     findOne(@Param('id') id: string) {}\n179: \n180:     @Post() // POST /users\n181:     @HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED) // 201\n182:     create(@Body() dto: CreateDto) {}\n183: \n184:     @Patch(':id') // PATCH /users/:id\n185:     update(@Param('id') id: string, @Body() dto: UpdateDto) {}\n186: \n187:     @Delete(':id') // DELETE /users/:id\n188:     remove(@Param('id') id: string) {}\n189: }\n190: ```\n191: \n192: ### Parameter Decorators\n193: \n194: ```typescript\n195: import { Param, Body, Query, Headers, Req, Res } from '@nestjs/common';\n196: \n197: @Controller('users')\n198: export class UserController {\n199:     @Get(':id')\n200:     findOne(\n201:         @Param('id') id: string, // Route parameter\n202:         @Query('include') include?: string, // Query parameter\n203:         @Headers('authorization') auth?: string, // Header\n204:     ) {}\n205: \n206:     @Post()\n207:     create(\n208:         @Body() createDto: CreateUserDto, // Request body\n209:     ) {}\n210: \n211:     @Get()\n212:     findAll(\n213:         @Query() query: PaginationDto, // All query params as DTO\n214:     ) {}\n215: }\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ### Validation Pipes\n219: \n220: ```typescript\n221: import { ParseUUIDPipe, ParseIntPipe, ValidationPipe } from '@nestjs/common';\n222: \n223: @Controller('users')\n224: export class UserController {\n225:     @Get(':id')\n226:     findOne(\n227:         @Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string, // Auto-validate UUID\n228:     ) {}\n229: \n230:     @Get()\n231:     findAll(\n232:         @Query('page', ParseIntPipe) page: number, // Auto-parse to integer\n233:     ) {}\n234: \n235:     @Post()\n236:     create(\n237:         @Body() dto: CreateUserDto, // ValidationPipe runs globally\n238:     ) {}\n239: }\n240: ```\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ## Custom Decorators\n245: \n246: ### @Public() - Bypass Authentication\n247: \n248: ```typescript\n249: import { Public } from 'src/core/decorators';\n250: \n251: @Controller('users')\n252: export class UserController {\n253:     @Public() // This route doesn't require authentication\n254:     @Post()\n255:     async create(@Body() createUserDto: CreateUserDto) {\n256:         return await this.userService.createUser(createUserDto);\n257:     }\n258: \n259:     @Get(':id') // This route requires authentication (default)\n260:     async findOne(@Param('id') id: string) {\n261:         return await this.userService.findById(id);\n262:     }\n263: }\n264: ```\n265: \n266: ### @Roles() - Role-Based Access Control\n267: \n268: ```typescript\n269: import { Roles } from 'src/core/decorators';\n270: \n271: @Controller('users')\n272: export class UserController {\n273:     @Roles('admin') // Only admins can access\n274:     @Delete(':id')\n275:     async remove(@Param('id') id: string) {\n276:         return await this.userService.remove(id);\n277:     }\n278: \n279:     @Roles('admin', 'operations') // Multiple roles\n280:     @Patch(':id')\n281:     async update(@Param('id') id: string, @Body() dto: UpdateUserDto) {\n282:         return await this.userService.update(id, dto);\n283:     }\n284: }\n285: ```\n286: \n287: ### @CurrentUser() - Get Authenticated User\n288: \n289: ```typescript\n290: import { CurrentUser } from 'src/core/decorators';\n291: import { IJwtPayload } from '@shared/interfaces';\n292: \n293: @Controller('profile')\n294: export class ProfileController {\n295:     @Get()\n296:     async getProfile(@CurrentUser() user: IJwtPayload) {\n297:         // user contains: { userId, email, roles, ... }\n298:         return await this.userService.findById(user.userId);\n299:     }\n300: \n301:     @Patch()\n302:     async updateProfile(\n303:         @CurrentUser() user: IJwtPayload,\n304:         @Body() dto: UpdateProfileDto,\n305:     ) {\n306:         return await this.userService.update(user.userId, dto);\n307:     }\n308: }\n309: ```\n310: \n311: ### @ApiSwagger() - Swagger Documentation\n312: \n313: ```typescript\n314: import { ApiSwagger } from 'src/core/decorators';\n315: \n316: @Controller('users')\n317: export class UserController {\n318:     @Post()\n319:     @ApiSwagger({\n320:         resourceName: 'User',\n321:         operation: 'create',\n322:         requestDto: CreateUserDto,\n323:         responseDto: UserResponseDto,\n324:         successStatus: 201,\n325:         errors: [\n326:             { status: 400, description: 'Invalid input data' },\n327:             { status: 409, description: 'Email already exists' },\n328:         ],\n329:     })\n330:     async create(@Body() dto: CreateUserDto) {\n331:         return await this.userService.create(dto);\n332:     }\n333: }\n334: ```\n335: \n336: ---\n337: \n338: ## Good Examples\n339: \n340: ### Example 1: User Controller (Excellent ✅)\n341: \n342: **File:** `src/modules/users/user.controller.ts`\n343: \n344: ```typescript\n345: import {\n346:     Controller,\n347:     Get,\n348:     Post,\n349:     Body,\n350:     Patch,\n351:     Param,\n352:     Query,\n353:     Delete,\n354:     HttpCode,\n355:     HttpStatus,\n356:     ParseUUIDPipe,\n357: } from '@nestjs/common';\n358: import { ApiTags } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n359: import { BaseController } from 'src/core/base';\n360: import { ApiSwagger, Public } from 'src/core/decorators';\n361: import { ResponsePayloadDto } from '@shared/dtos';\n362: import { UserService } from './user.service';\n363: import { CreateUserDto, UpdateUserDto, UserResponseDto } from './dtos';\n364: import { User } from './user.entity';\n365: \n366: @ApiTags('Users')\n367: @Controller('users')\n368: export class UserController extends BaseController<\n369:     User,\n370:     CreateUserDto,\n371:     UpdateUserDto\n372: > {\n373:     constructor(private readonly userService: UserService) {\n374:         super(userService);\n375:     }\n376: \n377:     // Override create to make it public and use custom service method\n378:     @Public()\n379:     @Post()\n380:     @HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)\n381:     @ApiSwagger({\n382:         resourceName: 'User',\n383:         operation: 'create',\n384:         requestDto: CreateUserDto,\n385:         responseDto: UserResponseDto,\n386:         successStatus: 201,\n387:         errors: [\n388:             { status: 400, description: 'Invalid input data' },\n389:             { status: 409, description: 'User with this email already exists' },\n390:         ],\n391:     })\n392:     async create(\n393:         @Body() createUserDto: CreateUserDto,\n394:     ): Promise<ResponsePayloadDto<User>> {\n395:         return await this.userService.createUser(createUserDto);\n396:     }\n397: \n398:     // Custom endpoint: Get active users\n399:     @Get('active')\n400:     @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n401:     @ApiSwagger({\n402:         resourceName: 'Active Users',\n403:         operation: 'getAll',\n404:         responseDto: UserResponseDto,\n405:         isArray: true,\n406:     })\n407:     async getActiveUsers() {\n408:         return this.userService.getActiveUsers();\n409:     }\n410: \n411:     // Custom endpoint: Search by email\n412:     @Get('search')\n413:     @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n414:     @ApiSwagger({\n415:         resourceName: 'Users',\n416:         operation: 'search',\n417:         summary: 'Search users by email',\n418:         responseDto: UserResponseDto,\n419:         isArray: true,\n420:     })\n421:     async searchByEmail(@Query('email') email: string) {\n422:         if (!email) return [];\n423:         const user = await this.userService.findByEmail(email);\n424:         return user ? [user] : [];\n425:     }\n426: \n427:     // Inherited CRUD endpoints:\n428:     // - GET /users (with pagination)\n429:     // - GET /users/:id\n430:     // - PATCH /users/:id\n431:     // - DELETE /users/:id\n432: }\n433: ```\n434: \n435: **What Makes This Excellent:**\n436: \n437: - ✅ Extends BaseController for automatic CRUD\n438: - ✅ Custom endpoints added where needed\n439: - ✅ Proper use of @Public decorator\n440: - ✅ Complete Swagger documentation\n441: - ✅ Clean parameter extraction\n442: - ✅ Zero business logic\n443: \n444: ### Example 2: Authentication Controller (Good ✅)\n445: \n446: **File:** `src/modules/auth/auth.controller.ts`\n447: \n448: ```typescript\n449: import {\n450:     Body,\n451:     Controller,\n452:     Get,\n453:     Post,\n454:     UseGuards,\n455:     UseInterceptors,\n456: } from '@nestjs/common';\n457: import { ApiTags } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n458: import { AuthService } from './auth.service';\n459: import { LoginDto, SocialLoginDto } from './dtos';\n460: import { ApiSwagger, CurrentUser, Public } from '@core/decorators';\n461: import { JwtAuthGuard } from '@core/guards';\n462: import { SetToken, RemoveToken } from '@core/interceptors';\n463: import { IJwtPayload } from '@shared/interfaces';\n464: import { LoginResponsePayloadDto, ResponsePayloadDto } from '@shared/dtos';\n465: \n466: @ApiTags('Authentication')\n467: @Controller('auth')\n468: export class AuthController {\n469:     constructor(private authService: AuthService) {}\n470: \n471:     @Post('login')\n472:     @Public()\n473:     @UseInterceptors(SetToken)\n474:     @ApiSwagger({\n475:         resourceName: 'Login',\n476:         operation: 'custom',\n477:         summary: 'User login',\n478:         requestDto: LoginDto,\n479:         responseDto: LoginResponsePayloadDto,\n480:         requiresAuth: false,\n481:         errors: [{ status: 401, description: 'Incorrect email or password' }],\n482:     })\n483:     async login(\n484:         @Body() dto: LoginDto,\n485:     ): Promise<ResponsePayloadDto<LoginResponsePayloadDto>> {\n486:         return await this.authService.login(dto);\n487:     }\n488: \n489:     @Post('social-login')\n490:     @Public()\n491:     @UseInterceptors(SetToken)\n492:     @ApiSwagger({\n493:         resourceName: 'Social Login',\n494:         operation: 'custom',\n495:         summary: 'Social login (Google, Kakao, Naver)',\n496:         requestDto: SocialLoginDto,\n497:         responseDto: LoginResponsePayloadDto,\n498:         requiresAuth: false,\n499:     })\n500:     async socialLogin(\n501:         @Body() dto: SocialLoginDto,\n502:     ): Promise<LoginResponsePayloadDto> {\n503:         return await this.authService.socialLogin(dto);\n504:     }\n505: \n506:     @Get('check-login')\n507:     @UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)\n508:     @ApiSwagger({\n509:         resourceName: 'Check Login',\n510:         operation: 'custom',\n511:         summary: 'Check if user is logged in',\n512:         responseDto: LoginResponsePayloadDto,\n513:         requiresAuth: true,\n514:     })\n515:     async checkUserLogin(@CurrentUser() user: IJwtPayload | null) {\n516:         if (user) {\n517:             return await this.authService.getUserInformation(user);\n518:         }\n519:         return null;\n520:     }\n521: \n522:     @Get('logout')\n523:     @UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard)\n524:     @UseInterceptors(RemoveToken)\n525:     @ApiSwagger({\n526:         resourceName: 'Logout',\n527:         operation: 'custom',\n528:         summary: 'Logout user',\n529:         requiresAuth: true,\n530:     })\n531:     async logout(@CurrentUser() user: IJwtPayload | null) {\n532:         return await this.authService.logout(user);\n533:     }\n534: }\n535: ```\n536: \n537: **What Makes This Good:**\n538: \n539: - ✅ Clear route definitions\n540: - ✅ Proper use of @Public decorator\n541: - ✅ Interceptors for token management\n542: - ✅ @CurrentUser decorator for auth\n543: - ✅ Complete Swagger documentation\n544: - ✅ All logic delegated to service\n545: \n546: ---\n547: \n548: ## Anti-Patterns\n549: \n550: ### Anti-Pattern 1: Business Logic in Controller (Bad ❌)\n551: \n552: ```typescript\n553: // ❌ ANTI-PATTERN: Business logic in controller\n554: @Post()\n555: async create(@Body() createUserDto: CreateUserDto) {\n556:     // ❌ Email validation in controller\n557:     const emailRegex = /^[^\\s@]+@[^\\s@]+\\.[^\\s@]+$/;\n558:     if (!emailRegex.test(createUserDto.email)) {\n559:         throw new BadRequestException('Invalid email format');\n560:     }\n561: \n562:     // ❌ Business rule checking in controller\n563:     const existing = await this.userService.findByEmail(createUserDto.email);\n564:     if (existing) {\n565:         throw new ConflictException('Email already exists');\n566:     }\n567: \n568:     // ❌ Data transformation in controller\n569:     const hashedPassword = await bcrypt.hash(createUserDto.password, 10);\n570:     const userData = {\n571:         ...createUserDto,\n572:         password: hashedPassword,\n573:         isActive: true,\n574:     };\n575: \n576:     // Finally create user\n577:     return await this.userService.create(userData);\n578: }\n579: ```\n580: \n581: **Why This Is Terrible:**\n582: \n583: - Violates single responsibility principle\n584: - Business logic not reusable\n585: - Hard to test\n586: - Mixes HTTP concerns with business rules\n587: \n588: **How to Fix:**\n589: \n590: ```typescript\n591: // ✅ GOOD: Delegate to service\n592: @Post()\n593: async create(@Body() createUserDto: CreateUserDto) {\n594:     return await this.userService.createUser(createUserDto);\n595: }\n596: \n597: // Service handles all business logic:\n598: // - Email validation (via DTO with class-validator)\n599: // - Duplicate checking\n600: // - Password hashing\n601: // - Setting defaults\n602: ```\n603: \n604: ### Anti-Pattern 2: Not Using BaseController (Bad ❌)\n605: \n606: ```typescript\n607: // ❌ ANTI-PATTERN: Reimplementing CRUD manually\n608: @Controller('products')\n609: export class ProductController {\n610:     constructor(private productService: ProductService) {}\n611: \n612:     @Post()\n613:     async create(@Body() dto: CreateProductDto) {\n614:         try {\n615:             const product = await this.productService.create(dto);\n616:             return {\n617:                 success: true,\n618:                 statusCode: 201,\n619:                 message: 'Product created',\n620:                 data: product,\n621:             };\n622:         } catch (error) {\n623:             throw new InternalServerErrorException('Failed to create product');\n624:         }\n625:     }\n626: \n627:     @Get()\n628:     async findAll(@Query('page') page = 1, @Query('limit') limit = 10) {\n629:         const products = await this.productService.findAll();\n630:         // Manual pagination logic...\n631:         return {\n632:             success: true,\n633:             data: products,\n634:             page,\n635:             limit,\n636:         };\n637:     }\n638: \n639:     // ... 200 more lines of manual CRUD\n640: }\n641: ```\n642: \n643: **How to Fix:**\n644: \n645: ```typescript\n646: // ✅ GOOD: Use BaseController\n647: @ApiTags('Products')\n648: @Controller('products')\n649: export class ProductController extends BaseController<\n650:     Product,\n651:     CreateProductDto,\n652:     UpdateProductDto\n653: > {\n654:     constructor(private readonly productService: ProductService) {\n655:         super(productService);\n656:     }\n657: \n658:     // All CRUD operations inherited!\n659:     // Only add custom endpoints if needed\n660: }\n661: ```\n662: \n663: ---\n664: \n665: ## Swagger Documentation\n666: \n667: ### Complete Swagger Example\n668: \n669: ```typescript\n670: import {\n671:     ApiTags,\n672:     ApiOperation,\n673:     ApiResponse,\n674:     ApiBearerAuth,\n675: } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n676: import { ApiSwagger } from 'src/core/decorators';\n677: \n678: @ApiTags('Users')\n679: @ApiBearerAuth() // Requires authentication by default\n680: @Controller('users')\n681: export class UserController extends BaseController<\n682:     User,\n683:     CreateUserDto,\n684:     UpdateUserDto\n685: > {\n686:     constructor(private readonly userService: UserService) {\n687:         super(userService);\n688:     }\n689: \n690:     @Post()\n691:     @ApiSwagger({\n692:         resourceName: 'User',\n693:         operation: 'create',\n694:         requestDto: CreateUserDto,\n695:         responseDto: UserResponseDto,\n696:         successStatus: 201,\n697:         errors: [\n698:             { status: 400, description: 'Invalid input data' },\n699:             { status: 409, description: 'User already exists' },\n700:         ],\n701:     })\n702:     async create(@Body() dto: CreateUserDto) {\n703:         return await this.userService.create(dto);\n704:     }\n705: \n706:     // Or use standard NestJS decorators:\n707:     @Get(':id')\n708:     @ApiOperation({ summary: 'Get user by ID' })\n709:     @ApiResponse({\n710:         status: 200,\n711:         description: 'User found',\n712:         type: UserResponseDto,\n713:     })\n714:     @ApiResponse({ status: 404, description: 'User not found' })\n715:     async findOne(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string) {\n716:         return await this.userService.findById(id);\n717:     }\n718: }\n719: ```\n720: \n721: ### Swagger DTO Example\n722: \n723: ```typescript\n724: import { ApiProperty } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n725: import { IsEmail, IsString, MinLength, MaxLength } from 'class-validator';\n726: \n727: export class CreateUserDto {\n728:     @ApiProperty({\n729:         example: 'user@example.com',\n730:         description: 'User email address',\n731:     })\n732:     @IsEmail()\n733:     email: string;\n734: \n735:     @ApiProperty({\n736:         example: 'John Doe',\n737:         description: 'User full name',\n738:         minLength: 2,\n739:         maxLength: 100,\n740:     })\n741:     @IsString()\n742:     @MinLength(2)\n743:     @MaxLength(100)\n744:     name: string;\n745: \n746:     @ApiProperty({\n747:         example: 'SecurePassword123',\n748:         description: 'User password',\n749:         minLength: 8,\n750:     })\n751:     @IsString()\n752:     @MinLength(8)\n753:     password: string;\n754: }\n755: ```\n756: \n757: ---\n758: \n759: ## Override Pattern\n760: \n761: ### When to Override BaseController Methods\n762: \n763: Override inherited methods when you need:\n764: \n765: - Custom business logic\n766: - Different response format\n767: - Additional validation\n768: - Custom error handling\n769: - Integration with other services\n770: \n771: ### Override Example\n772: \n773: ```typescript\n774: @ApiTags('Users')\n775: @Controller('users')\n776: export class UserController extends BaseController<\n777:     User,\n778:     CreateUserDto,\n779:     UpdateUserDto\n780: > {\n781:     constructor(\n782:         private readonly userService: UserService,\n783:         private readonly mailService: MailService,\n784:     ) {\n785:         super(userService);\n786:     }\n787: \n788:     // Override create to add email notification\n789:     @Public()\n790:     @Post()\n791:     @HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)\n792:     @ApiSwagger({\n793:         resourceName: 'User',\n794:         operation: 'create',\n795:         responseDto: UserResponseDto,\n796:     })\n797:     async create(\n798:         @Body() createUserDto: CreateUserDto,\n799:     ): Promise<ResponsePayloadDto<User>> {\n800:         // Create user\n801:         const result = await this.userService.createUser(createUserDto);\n802: \n803:         // Send welcome email (custom logic)\n804:         await this.mailService.sendWelcome(createUserDto.email);\n805: \n806:         return result;\n807:     }\n808: \n809:     // Override update to add logging\n810:     @Patch(':id')\n811:     @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n812:     @ApiSwagger({\n813:         resourceName: 'User',\n814:         operation: 'update',\n815:         responseDto: UserResponseDto,\n816:     })\n817:     async update(\n818:         @Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string,\n819:         @Body() updateUserDto: UpdateUserDto,\n820:         @CurrentUser() user: IJwtPayload,\n821:     ): Promise<ResponsePayloadDto<User>> {\n822:         // Update user\n823:         const updatedUser = await this.userService.updateUser(\n824:             id,\n825:             updateUserDto,\n826:         );\n827: \n828:         // Log action\n829:         console.log(`User ${user.userId} updated user ${id}`);\n830: \n831:         return new ResponsePayloadDto({\n832:             success: true,\n833:             statusCode: 200,\n834:             message: 'User updated successfully',\n835:             data: updatedUser,\n836:             timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n837:         });\n838:     }\n839: \n840:     // Keep other CRUD operations from BaseController:\n841:     // - findAll (GET /)\n842:     // - findOne (GET /:id)\n843:     // - remove (DELETE /:id)\n844: }\n845: ```\n846: \n847: ---\n848: \n849: ## Best Practices Summary\n850: \n851: ### ✅ DO:\n852: \n853: - Extend BaseController for all CRUD endpoints\n854: - Use NestJS decorators (@Get, @Post, @Body, @Param)\n855: - Use custom decorators (@Public, @Roles, @CurrentUser)\n856: - Add @ApiSwagger for documentation\n857: - Delegate all logic to services\n858: - Override base methods only when necessary\n859: - Use ParseUUIDPipe for ID validation\n860: - Return DTOs from methods\n861: \n862: ### ❌ DON'T:\n863: \n864: - Put business logic in controllers\n865: - Access database directly\n866: - Handle complex validations (use DTOs)\n867: - Format responses manually (interceptor does this)\n868: - Use process.env directly\n869: - Implement CRUD manually (use BaseController)\n870: - Forget @ApiTags decorator\n871: - Mix HTTP concerns with business rules\n872: \n873: ---\n874: \n875: ---\n876: \n877: ## MANDATORY: Controller Rules (from Base Architecture)\n878: \n879: ### Controller Size Limit: 200 Lines\n880: \n881: If a controller exceeds 200 lines, split into sub-controllers by feature area:\n882: - `UserController` (CRUD) + `UserProfileController` (profile-specific)\n883: - `OrderController` (CRUD) + `OrderPaymentController` (payment-specific)\n884: \n885: ### Swagger on EVERY Method\n886: \n887: ```typescript\n888: @ApiOperation({ summary: 'Get user by ID' })\n889: @ApiResponse({ status: 200, description: 'User found', type: UserResponseDto })\n890: @ApiResponse({ status: 404, description: 'User not found' })\n891: @Get(':id')\n892: findOne(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string) {\n893:   return this.userService.findOne(id);\n894: }\n895: ```\n896: \n897: No controller method without `@ApiOperation` and at least one `@ApiResponse`.\n898: \n899: ### Rate Limiting on Public Endpoints\n900: \n901: ```typescript\n902: import { Throttle } from '@nestjs/throttler';\n903: \n904: @Public()\n905: @Throttle({ default: { limit: 10, ttl: 60000 } })\n906: @Post('login')\n907: login(@Body() dto: LoginDto) { ... }\n908: ```\n909: \n910: Apply to: login, register, forgot-password, verify-email, resend-verification.\n911: \n912: ### Proper HTTP Status Codes\n913: \n914: | Operation | Status | Decorator |\n915: |-----------|--------|-----------|\n916: | Create | 201 | `@HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)` |\n917: | Update | 200 | (default) |\n918: | Delete | 204 | `@HttpCode(HttpStatus.NO_CONTENT)` |\n919: | List | 200 | (default) |\n920: | Not Found | 404 | Throw `NotFoundException` from service |\n921: \n922: ---\n923: \n924: **Related Files:**\n925: \n926: - [SKILL.md](../SKILL.md) - Main guide\n927: - [architecture-overview.md](architecture-overview.md) - Four-layer architecture\n928: - [services-and-repositories.md](services-and-repositories.md) - Service layer patterns\n929: - [validation-patterns.md](validation-patterns.md) - DTO validation\n\n(End of file - total 929 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Routing and Controllers - NestJS Best Practices\n\nComplete guide to NestJS controllers with BaseController pattern and decorators.\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n- [NestJS Controllers Overview](#nestjs-controllers-overview)\n- [BaseController Pattern](#basecontroller-pattern)\n- [Route Decorators](#route-decorators)\n- [Custom Decorators](#custom-decorators)\n- [Good Examples](#good-examples)\n- [Anti-Patterns](#anti-patterns)\n- [Swagger Documentation](#swagger-documentation)\n- [Override Pattern](#override-pattern)\n\n---\n\n## NestJS Controllers Overview\n\n### The Golden Rule","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/nestjs/guides/routing-and-controllers.md","time":{"start":1779187313790,"end":1779187314091}},"id":"prt_e3fd3e6c9001WphUzHr0oub5zx","sessionID":"ses_1c02c8023ffenJEyiMDWsaqbGv","messageID":"msg_e3fd384c2001epneAUIDsTOGpZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779187315819,"sessionID":"ses_1c02c8023ffenJEyiMDWsaqbGv","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_04_RlJ6m5ckiTu0QN0bSpGb7073","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/services-and-repositories.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/services-and-repositories.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Services and Repositories - NestJS Business Logic Layer\n2: \n3: Complete guide to organizing business logic with BaseService and data access with BaseRepository in NestJS.\n4: \n5: ## Table of Contents\n6: \n7: - [Service Layer Overview](#service-layer-overview)\n8: - [BaseService Pattern](#baseservice-pattern)\n9: - [Repository Pattern](#repository-pattern)\n10: - [Dependency Injection](#dependency-injection)\n11: - [Service Design Principles](#service-design-principles)\n12: - [Testing Services](#testing-services)\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Service Layer Overview\n17: \n18: ### Purpose of Services\n19: \n20: **Services contain business logic** - the 'what' and 'why' of your application:\n21: \n22: ```\n23: Controller asks: \"Create a user with this data\"\n24: Service answers: \"First I'll check if email exists, validate roles, hash password, then create\"\n25: Repository executes: \"Here's the saved user entity\"\n26: ```\n27: \n28: **Services are responsible for:**\n29: \n30: - ✅ Business logic implementation\n31: - ✅ Business rules enforcement\n32: - ✅ Orchestrating multiple repositories\n33: - ✅ Transaction management\n34: - ✅ Complex calculations\n35: - ✅ External service integration\n36: - ✅ Business validations\n37: \n38: **Services should NOT:**\n39: \n40: - ❌ Know about HTTP (Request/Response)\n41: - ❌ Direct TypeORM access (use repositories)\n42: - ❌ Handle route-specific logic\n43: - ❌ Format HTTP responses\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## BaseService Pattern\n48: \n49: ### Why BaseService?\n50: \n51: **Benefits:**\n52: \n53: - ✅ **90% less code** - CRUD operations automatic\n54: - ✅ **Consistent patterns** - Same methods across all services\n55: - ✅ **Type-safe** - Generic types throughout\n56: - ✅ **Easy to extend** - Add custom methods\n57: - ✅ **Error handling** - Built-in NotFoundException\n58: - ✅ **Relations support** - Load related entities automatically\n59: \n60: ### BaseService Template\n61: \n62: ```typescript\n63: // src/core/base/base.service.ts\n64: import { NotFoundException } from '@nestjs/common';\n65: import { BaseRepository } from './base.repository';\n66: import { BaseEntity } from './base.entity';\n67: import { FindManyOptions, DeepPartial, FindOptionsRelations } from 'typeorm';\n68: \n69: export abstract class BaseService<T extends BaseEntity> {\n70:     constructor(\n71:         protected readonly repository: BaseRepository<T>,\n72:         protected readonly entityName: string,\n73:     ) {}\n74: \n75:     // Override this to specify default relations\n76:     protected defaultRelations?: FindOptionsRelations<T>;\n77: \n78:     async findByIdOrFail(\n79:         id: string,\n80:         relations?: FindOptionsRelations<T>,\n81:     ): Promise<T> {\n82:         const entity = await this.repository.findById(\n83:             id,\n84:             relations || this.defaultRelations,\n85:         );\n86:         if (!entity) {\n87:             throw new NotFoundException(\n88:                 `${this.entityName} with ID ${id} not found`,\n89:             );\n90:         }\n91:         return entity;\n92:     }\n93: \n94:     async findAll(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<T[]> {\n95:         return this.repository.findAll({\n96:             ...options,\n97:             relations: options?.relations || this.defaultRelations,\n98:         });\n99:     }\n100: \n101:     async create(data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T> {\n102:         return this.repository.create(data);\n103:     }\n104: \n105:     async update(id: string, data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T | null> {\n106:         await this.findByIdOrFail(id); // Ensure entity exists\n107:         const updated = await this.repository.update(id, data);\n108:         return updated;\n109:     }\n110: \n111:     async remove(id: string): Promise<void> {\n112:         await this.findByIdOrFail(id); // Ensure entity exists\n113:         await this.repository.softDelete(id);\n114:     }\n115: \n116:     async delete(id: string): Promise<void> {\n117:         await this.findByIdOrFail(id); // Ensure entity exists\n118:         await this.repository.delete(id);\n119:     }\n120: }\n121: ```\n122: \n123: ### Using BaseService\n124: \n125: ```typescript\n126: // src/modules/users/user.service.ts\n127: import { Injectable, ConflictException } from '@nestjs/common';\n128: import { BaseService } from 'src/core/base';\n129: import { User } from './user.entity';\n130: import { UserRepository } from './user.repository';\n131: import { CreateUserDto } from './dtos';\n132: \n133: @Injectable()\n134: export class UserService extends BaseService<User> {\n135:     constructor(protected readonly repository: UserRepository) {\n136:         super(repository, 'User');\n137:     }\n138: \n139:     // Inherited methods available:\n140:     // - create(data)\n141:     // - findAll(options)\n142:     // - findByIdOrFail(id)\n143:     // - update(id, data)\n144:     // - remove(id)      // soft delete\n145:     // - delete(id)      // hard delete\n146: \n147:     // Add custom business logic:\n148:     async createUser(data: CreateUserDto): Promise<User> {\n149:         // Business rule: Check if email already exists\n150:         const existing = await this.repository.findOne({\n151:             where: { email: data.email },\n152:         });\n153: \n154:         if (existing) {\n155:             throw new ConflictException('Email already exists');\n156:         }\n157: \n158:         // Business rule: Validate roles\n159:         if (data.roles && !this.areValidRoles(data.roles)) {\n160:             throw new BadRequestException('Invalid roles');\n161:         }\n162: \n163:         // Create user\n164:         return this.repository.create(data);\n165:     }\n166: \n167:     async findByEmail(email: string): Promise<User | null> {\n168:         return this.repository.findOne({ where: { email } });\n169:     }\n170: \n171:     async getActiveUsers(): Promise<User[]> {\n172:         return this.repository.findAll({\n173:             where: { isActive: true },\n174:         });\n175:     }\n176: \n177:     private areValidRoles(roles: string[]): boolean {\n178:         const validRoles = ['user', 'admin', 'operations'];\n179:         return roles.every((role) => validRoles.includes(role));\n180:     }\n181: }\n182: ```\n183: \n184: ### Service with Relations\n185: \n186: ```typescript\n187: @Injectable()\n188: export class UserService extends BaseService<User> {\n189:     // Define default relations to load\n190:     protected defaultRelations = {\n191:         profile: true,\n192:         roles: true,\n193:     };\n194: \n195:     constructor(protected readonly repository: UserRepository) {\n196:         super(repository, 'User');\n197:     }\n198: \n199:     // Now all methods automatically load relations:\n200:     async findByIdOrFail(id: string): Promise<User> {\n201:         // Returns user with profile and roles loaded\n202:         return super.findByIdOrFail(id);\n203:     }\n204: \n205:     // Or override to load specific relations:\n206:     async findUserWithOrders(id: string): Promise<User> {\n207:         return this.findByIdOrFail(id, {\n208:             profile: true,\n209:             orders: {\n210:                 items: true,\n211:             },\n212:         });\n213:     }\n214: }\n215: ```\n216: \n217: ---\n218: \n219: ## Repository Pattern\n220: \n221: ### Purpose of Repositories\n222: \n223: **Repositories abstract data access** - the 'how' of data operations:\n224: \n225: ```\n226: Service: \"Get me all active users sorted by name\"\n227: Repository: \"Here's the TypeORM query that does that\"\n228: ```\n229: \n230: **Repositories are responsible for:**\n231: \n232: - ✅ All TypeORM operations\n233: - ✅ Query construction\n234: - ✅ Query optimization (select, relations)\n235: - ✅ Database error handling\n236: - ✅ Custom queries\n237: \n238: **Repositories should NOT:**\n239: \n240: - ❌ Contain business logic\n241: - ❌ Know about HTTP\n242: - ❌ Make business decisions\n243: \n244: ### BaseRepository Pattern\n245: \n246: ```typescript\n247: // src/core/base/base.repository.ts\n248: import {\n249:     Repository,\n250:     FindManyOptions,\n251:     FindOneOptions,\n252:     DeepPartial,\n253: } from 'typeorm';\n254: import { BaseEntity } from './base.entity';\n255: \n256: export abstract class BaseRepository<T extends BaseEntity> {\n257:     constructor(protected readonly repository: Repository<T>) {}\n258: \n259:     async findAll(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<T[]> {\n260:         return this.repository.find(options);\n261:     }\n262: \n263:     async findById(id: string, relations?: any): Promise<T | null> {\n264:         return this.repository.findOne({\n265:             where: { id } as any,\n266:             relations,\n267:         });\n268:     }\n269: \n270:     async findOne(options: FindOneOptions<T>): Promise<T | null> {\n271:         return this.repository.findOne(options);\n272:     }\n273: \n274:     async create(data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T> {\n275:         const entity = this.repository.create(data);\n276:         return this.repository.save(entity);\n277:     }\n278: \n279:     async update(id: string, data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T | null> {\n280:         await this.repository.update(id, data as any);\n281:         return this.findById(id);\n282:     }\n283: \n284:     async softDelete(id: string): Promise<void> {\n285:         await this.repository.softDelete(id);\n286:     }\n287: \n288:     async delete(id: string): Promise<void> {\n289:         await this.repository.delete(id);\n290:     }\n291: }\n292: ```\n293: \n294: ### Using BaseRepository\n295: \n296: ```typescript\n297: // src/modules/users/user.repository.ts\n298: import { Injectable } from '@nestjs/common';\n299: import { InjectRepository } from '@nestjs/typeorm';\n300: import { Repository } from 'typeorm';\n301: import { BaseRepository } from 'src/core/base';\n302: import { User } from './user.entity';\n303: \n304: @Injectable()\n305: export class UserRepository extends BaseRepository<User> {\n306:     constructor(\n307:         @InjectRepository(User)\n308:         repository: Repository<User>,\n309:     ) {\n310:         super(repository);\n311:     }\n312: \n313:     // Inherited methods:\n314:     // - findAll(options)\n315:     // - findById(id)\n316:     // - findOne(options)\n317:     // - create(data)\n318:     // - update(id, data)\n319:     // - softDelete(id)\n320:     // - delete(id)\n321: \n322:     // Add custom queries:\n323:     async findByEmail(email: string): Promise<User | null> {\n324:         return this.findOne({ where: { email } });\n325:     }\n326: \n327:     async findActiveUsers(): Promise<User[]> {\n328:         return this.findAll({\n329:             where: { isActive: true },\n330:             order: { createdAt: 'DESC' },\n331:         });\n332:     }\n333: \n334:     async findWithRoles(userId: string): Promise<User | null> {\n335:         return this.repository.findOne({\n336:             where: { id: userId },\n337:             relations: { roles: true },\n338:         });\n339:     }\n340: \n341:     async countByRole(role: string): Promise<number> {\n342:         return this.repository\n343:             .createQueryBuilder('user')\n344:             .where(':role = ANY(user.roles)', { role })\n345:             .getCount();\n346:     }\n347: }\n348: ```\n349: \n350: ---\n351: \n352: ## Dependency Injection\n353: \n354: ### NestJS Dependency Injection Pattern\n355: \n356: NestJS uses constructor-based dependency injection:\n357: \n358: ```typescript\n359: @Injectable()\n360: export class UserService extends BaseService<User> {\n361:     constructor(\n362:         protected readonly repository: UserRepository,\n363:         private readonly mailService: MailService, // Inject services\n364:         private readonly tokenService: TokenService, // Multiple DI\n365:     ) {\n366:         super(repository, 'User');\n367:     }\n368: \n369:     async createUser(data: CreateUserDto): Promise<User> {\n370:         // Create user\n371:         const user = await this.repository.create(data);\n372: \n373:         // Use injected services\n374:         await this.mailService.sendWelcome(user.email);\n375:         const token = await this.tokenService.generate(user);\n376: \n377:         return user;\n378:     }\n379: }\n380: ```\n381: \n382: ### Module Configuration\n383: \n384: ```typescript\n385: // user.module.ts\n386: import { Module } from '@nestjs/common';\n387: import { TypeOrmModule } from '@nestjs/typeorm';\n388: import { User } from './user.entity';\n389: import { UserRepository } from './user.repository';\n390: import { UserService } from './user.service';\n391: import { UserController } from './user.controller';\n392: import { MailModule } from '@infrastructure/mail/mail.module';\n393: import { TokenModule } from '@infrastructure/token/token.module';\n394: \n395: @Module({\n396:     imports: [\n397:         TypeOrmModule.forFeature([User]), // Register entity\n398:         MailModule, // Import other modules\n399:         TokenModule,\n400:     ],\n401:     controllers: [UserController],\n402:     providers: [UserService, UserRepository],\n403:     exports: [UserService], // Export for use in other modules\n404: })\n405: export class UserModule {}\n406: ```\n407: \n408: ### Circular Dependency Handling\n409: \n410: When services depend on each other:\n411: \n412: ```typescript\n413: // user.service.ts\n414: import { Injectable, forwardRef, Inject } from '@nestjs/common';\n415: import { OrderService } from '../orders/order.service';\n416: \n417: @Injectable()\n418: export class UserService extends BaseService<User> {\n419:     constructor(\n420:         protected readonly repository: UserRepository,\n421:         @Inject(forwardRef(() => OrderService))\n422:         private readonly orderService: OrderService,\n423:     ) {\n424:         super(repository, 'User');\n425:     }\n426: \n427:     async getUserWithOrders(userId: string) {\n428:         const user = await this.findByIdOrFail(userId);\n429:         const orders = await this.orderService.findByUserId(userId);\n430:         return { ...user, orders };\n431:     }\n432: }\n433: ```\n434: \n435: ---\n436: \n437: ## Service Design Principles\n438: \n439: ### 1. Single Responsibility\n440: \n441: Each service should have ONE clear purpose:\n442: \n443: ```typescript\n444: // ✅ GOOD - Single responsibility\n445: @Injectable()\n446: export class UserService extends BaseService<User> {\n447:     async createUser() {}\n448:     async updateUser() {}\n449:     async deleteUser() {}\n450:     async findByEmail() {}\n451: }\n452: \n453: @Injectable()\n454: export class EmailService {\n455:     async sendEmail() {}\n456:     async sendBulkEmails() {}\n457: }\n458: \n459: // ❌ BAD - Too many responsibilities\n460: @Injectable()\n461: export class UserService extends BaseService<User> {\n462:     async createUser() {}\n463:     async sendWelcomeEmail() {} // Should be EmailService\n464:     async logUserActivity() {} // Should be AuditService\n465:     async processPayment() {} // Should be PaymentService\n466: }\n467: ```\n468: \n469: ### 2. Clear Method Names\n470: \n471: Method names should describe WHAT they do:\n472: \n473: ```typescript\n474: // ✅ GOOD - Clear intent\n475: async createUser(data: CreateUserDto): Promise<User>\n476: async findByEmail(email: string): Promise<User | null>\n477: async getActiveUsers(): Promise<User[]>\n478: async updateUserProfile(userId: string, data: UpdateProfileDto): Promise<User>\n479: \n480: // ❌ BAD - Vague or misleading\n481: async process(data: any): Promise<any>\n482: async handle(params: any): Promise<any>\n483: async doIt(): Promise<void>\n484: async execute(): Promise<any>\n485: ```\n486: \n487: ### 3. Return Types\n488: \n489: Always use explicit return types:\n490: \n491: ```typescript\n492: // ✅ GOOD - Explicit types\n493: async createUser(data: CreateUserDto): Promise<User> {\n494:     return this.repository.create(data);\n495: }\n496: \n497: async findUsers(): Promise<User[]> {\n498:     return this.repository.findAll();\n499: }\n500: \n501: async deleteUser(id: string): Promise<void> {\n502:     await this.repository.softDelete(id);\n503: }\n504: \n505: // ❌ BAD - Implicit any\n506: async createUser(data) {  // No types!\n507:     return this.repository.create(data);\n508: }\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ### 4. Error Handling\n512: \n513: Services should throw meaningful NestJS exceptions:\n514: \n515: ```typescript\n516: import {\n517:     NotFoundException,\n518:     ConflictException,\n519:     BadRequestException,\n520:     UnauthorizedException,\n521: } from '@nestjs/common';\n522: \n523: @Injectable()\n524: export class UserService extends BaseService<User> {\n525:     async createUser(data: CreateUserDto): Promise<User> {\n526:         // ✅ GOOD - Meaningful errors\n527:         const existing = await this.findByEmail(data.email);\n528:         if (existing) {\n529:             throw new ConflictException('Email already exists');\n530:         }\n531: \n532:         if (!this.areValidRoles(data.roles)) {\n533:             throw new BadRequestException('Invalid roles provided');\n534:         }\n535: \n536:         return this.repository.create(data);\n537:     }\n538: \n539:     async updateUser(id: string, data: UpdateUserDto): Promise<User> {\n540:         // ✅ Uses findByIdOrFail which throws NotFoundException\n541:         const user = await this.findByIdOrFail(id);\n542:         return this.repository.update(id, data);\n543:     }\n544: \n545:     // ❌ BAD - Generic errors\n546:     async badExample(id: string): Promise<User> {\n547:         const user = await this.repository.findById(id);\n548:         if (!user) {\n549:             throw new Error('Error'); // What error?\n550:         }\n551:         return user;\n552:     }\n553: }\n554: ```\n555: \n556: ### 5. Business Logic in Services\n557: \n558: Keep business logic in services, not controllers or repositories:\n559: \n560: ```typescript\n561: @Injectable()\n562: export class OrderService extends BaseService<Order> {\n563:     constructor(\n564:         protected readonly repository: OrderRepository,\n565:         private readonly productService: ProductService,\n566:         private readonly userService: UserService,\n567:     ) {\n568:         super(repository, 'Order');\n569:     }\n570: \n571:     async createOrder(userId: string, items: OrderItemDto[]): Promise<Order> {\n572:         // Business rule: Verify user exists\n573:         const user = await this.userService.findByIdOrFail(userId);\n574: \n575:         // Business rule: Verify all products exist and are available\n576:         for (const item of items) {\n577:             const product = await this.productService.findByIdOrFail(\n578:                 item.productId,\n579:             );\n580:             if (!product.isAvailable) {\n581:                 throw new BadRequestException(\n582:                     `Product ${product.name} is not available`,\n583:                 );\n584:             }\n585:             if (product.stock < item.quantity) {\n586:                 throw new BadRequestException(\n587:                     `Insufficient stock for ${product.name}`,\n588:                 );\n589:             }\n590:         }\n591: \n592:         // Business rule: Calculate total\n593:         const total = items.reduce((sum, item) => {\n594:             return sum + item.price * item.quantity;\n595:         }, 0);\n596: \n597:         // Business rule: Apply discount if eligible\n598:         const discount = await this.calculateDiscount(user, total);\n599:         const finalTotal = total - discount;\n600: \n601:         // Create order\n602:         return this.repository.create({\n603:             userId,\n604:             items,\n605:             total: finalTotal,\n606:             status: 'pending',\n607:         });\n608:     }\n609: \n610:     private async calculateDiscount(\n611:         user: User,\n612:         total: number,\n613:     ): Promise<number> {\n614:         // Business logic for discount calculation\n615:         if (user.isPremium && total > 100) {\n616:             return total * 0.1; // 10% discount\n617:         }\n618:         return 0;\n619:     }\n620: }\n621: ```\n622: \n623: ### 6. Transaction Management\n624: \n625: Handle transactions in services:\n626: \n627: ```typescript\n628: import { InjectRepository } from '@nestjs/typeorm';\n629: import { DataSource } from 'typeorm';\n630: \n631: @Injectable()\n632: export class OrderService extends BaseService<Order> {\n633:     constructor(\n634:         protected readonly repository: OrderRepository,\n635:         private readonly productService: ProductService,\n636:         private readonly dataSource: DataSource, // Inject DataSource for transactions\n637:     ) {\n638:         super(repository, 'Order');\n639:     }\n640: \n641:     async createOrderWithTransaction(\n642:         userId: string,\n643:         items: OrderItemDto[],\n644:     ): Promise<Order> {\n645:         const queryRunner = this.dataSource.createQueryRunner();\n646:         await queryRunner.connect();\n647:         await queryRunner.startTransaction();\n648: \n649:         try {\n650:             // Create order\n651:             const order = await queryRunner.manager.save(Order, {\n652:                 userId,\n653:                 items,\n654:                 status: 'pending',\n655:             });\n656: \n657:             // Update product stock\n658:             for (const item of items) {\n659:                 await queryRunner.manager.decrement(\n660:                     Product,\n661:                     { id: item.productId },\n662:                     'stock',\n663:                     item.quantity,\n664:                 );\n665:             }\n666: \n667:             // Commit transaction\n668:             await queryRunner.commitTransaction();\n669:             return order;\n670:         } catch (error) {\n671:             // Rollback on error\n672:             await queryRunner.rollbackTransaction();\n673:             throw error;\n674:         } finally {\n675:             // Release query runner\n676:             await queryRunner.release();\n677:         }\n678:     }\n679: }\n680: ```\n681: \n682: ---\n683: \n684: ## Testing Services\n685: \n686: ### Unit Testing Services\n687: \n688: ```typescript\n689: // user.service.spec.ts\n690: import { Test, TestingModule } from '@nestjs/testing';\n691: import { ConflictException, NotFoundException } from '@nestjs/common';\n692: import { UserService } from './user.service';\n693: import { UserRepository } from './user.repository';\n694: import { User } from './user.entity';\n695: \n696: describe('UserService', () => {\n697:     let service: UserService;\n698:     let repository: UserRepository;\n699: \n700:     const mockUserRepository = {\n701:         findOne: jest.fn(),\n702:         create: jest.fn(),\n703:         findById: jest.fn(),\n704:         update: jest.fn(),\n705:         softDelete: jest.fn(),\n706:     };\n707: \n708:     beforeEach(async () => {\n709:         const module: TestingModule = await Test.createTestingModule({\n710:             providers: [\n711:                 UserService,\n712:                 {\n713:                     provide: UserRepository,\n714:                     useValue: mockUserRepository,\n715:                 },\n716:             ],\n717:         }).compile();\n718: \n719:         service = module.get<UserService>(UserService);\n720:         repository = module.get<UserRepository>(UserRepository);\n721:     });\n722: \n723:     afterEach(() => {\n724:         jest.clearAllMocks();\n725:     });\n726: \n727:     describe('createUser', () => {\n728:         const createUserDto = {\n729:             email: 'test@example.com',\n730:             name: 'Test User',\n731:             password: 'password123',\n732:             roles: ['user'],\n733:         };\n734: \n735:         it('should create a user when email does not exist', async () => {\n736:             // Arrange\n737:             mockUserRepository.findOne.mockResolvedValue(null);\n738:             const createdUser = { id: 'uuid', ...createUserDto };\n739:             mockUserRepository.create.mockResolvedValue(createdUser);\n740: \n741:             // Act\n742:             const result = await service.createUser(createUserDto);\n743: \n744:             // Assert\n745:             expect(result).toEqual(createdUser);\n746:             expect(mockUserRepository.findOne).toHaveBeenCalledWith({\n747:                 where: { email: createUserDto.email },\n748:             });\n749:             expect(mockUserRepository.create).toHaveBeenCalledWith(\n750:                 createUserDto,\n751:             );\n752:         });\n753: \n754:         it('should throw ConflictException when email already exists', async () => {\n755:             // Arrange\n756:             mockUserRepository.findOne.mockResolvedValue({\n757:                 id: 'existing-uuid',\n758:             });\n759: \n760:             // Act & Assert\n761:             await expect(service.createUser(createUserDto)).rejects.toThrow(\n762:                 ConflictException,\n763:             );\n764:             expect(mockUserRepository.create).not.toHaveBeenCalled();\n765:         });\n766: \n767:         it('should throw BadRequestException for invalid roles', async () => {\n768:             // Arrange\n769:             const invalidDto = { ...createUserDto, roles: ['invalid-role'] };\n770:             mockUserRepository.findOne.mockResolvedValue(null);\n771: \n772:             // Act & Assert\n773:             await expect(service.createUser(invalidDto)).rejects.toThrow(\n774:                 BadRequestException,\n775:             );\n776:         });\n777:     });\n778: \n779:     describe('findByIdOrFail', () => {\n780:         it('should return user when found', async () => {\n781:             // Arrange\n782:             const user = { id: 'uuid', email: 'test@example.com' };\n783:             mockUserRepository.findById.mockResolvedValue(user);\n784: \n785:             // Act\n786:             const result = await service.findByIdOrFail('uuid');\n787: \n788:             // Assert\n789:             expect(result).toEqual(user);\n790:             expect(mockUserRepository.findById).toHaveBeenCalledWith(\n791:                 'uuid',\n792:                 undefined,\n793:             );\n794:         });\n795: \n796:         it('should throw NotFoundException when user not found', async () => {\n797:             // Arrange\n798:             mockUserRepository.findById.mockResolvedValue(null);\n799: \n800:             // Act & Assert\n801:             await expect(service.findByIdOrFail('uuid')).rejects.toThrow(\n802:                 NotFoundException,\n803:             );\n804:         });\n805:     });\n806: });\n807: ```\n808: \n809: ### Integration Testing\n810: \n811: ```typescript\n812: // user.service.integration.spec.ts\n813: import { Test, TestingModule } from '@nestjs/testing';\n814: import { TypeOrmModule } from '@nestjs/typeorm';\n815: import { UserService } from './user.service';\n816: import { UserRepository } from './user.repository';\n817: import { User } from './user.entity';\n818: \n819: describe('UserService Integration', () => {\n820:     let service: UserService;\n821:     let module: TestingModule;\n822: \n823:     beforeAll(async () => {\n824:         module = await Test.createTestingModule({\n825:             imports: [\n826:                 TypeOrmModule.forRoot({\n827:                     type: 'postgres',\n828:                     host: 'localhost',\n829:                     port: 5432,\n830:                     database: 'test_db',\n831:                     entities: [User],\n832:                     synchronize: true,\n833:                 }),\n834:                 TypeOrmModule.forFeature([User]),\n835:             ],\n836:             providers: [UserService, UserRepository],\n837:         }).compile();\n838: \n839:         service = module.get<UserService>(UserService);\n840:     });\n841: \n842:     afterAll(async () => {\n843:         await module.close();\n844:     });\n845: \n846:     it('should create and find user', async () => {\n847:         const userData = {\n848:             email: 'integration@example.com',\n849:             name: 'Integration Test',\n850:             password: 'password123',\n851:             roles: ['user'],\n852:         };\n853: \n854:         const created = await service.createUser(userData);\n855:         expect(created.id).toBeDefined();\n856: \n857:         const found = await service.findByIdOrFail(created.id);\n858:         expect(found.email).toBe(userData.email);\n859:     });\n860: });\n861: ```\n862: \n863: ---\n864: \n865: ## Best Practices Summary\n866: \n867: ### ✅ DO:\n868: \n869: - Extend BaseService for all entities\n870: - Use NestJS dependency injection\n871: - Throw NestJS exceptions (NotFoundException, ConflictException)\n872: - Keep business logic in services\n873: - Use explicit return types\n874: - Write unit tests for business logic\n875: - Use transactions for multi-step operations\n876: - Inject repositories, not TypeORM directly\n877: - Define defaultRelations for common includes\n878: \n879: ### ❌ DON'T:\n880: \n881: - Put business logic in controllers or repositories\n882: - Use new keyword to instantiate services\n883: - Access TypeORM directly in services (use repositories)\n884: - Return generic Error objects\n885: - Create \"god services\" with too many responsibilities\n886: - Forget to handle edge cases\n887: - Skip error handling\n888: - Use any types\n889: - Mix HTTP concerns with business logic\n890: \n891: ---\n892: \n893: ---\n894: \n895: ## MANDATORY: Service Rules (from Base Architecture)\n896: \n897: ### I18nHelper for ALL Exception Messages\n898: \n899: ```typescript\n900: // BAD\n901: throw new NotFoundException('User not found');\n902: throw new ConflictException(`Email ${email} already exists`);\n903: \n904: // GOOD\n905: throw new NotFoundException(I18nHelper.t('user.notFound'));\n906: throw new ConflictException(I18nHelper.t('user.emailAlreadyExists'));\n907: ```\n908: \n909: ### Service Size Limit: 300 Lines\n910: \n911: If a service exceeds 300 lines:\n912: 1. Extract domain helper services (e.g., `UserValidationService`, `UserNotificationService`)\n913: 2. Keep the main service as orchestrator\n914: 3. Inject helpers via constructor\n915: \n916: ### No Direct TypeORM in Services\n917: \n918: ```typescript\n919: // BAD: Using @InjectRepository directly in service\n920: @InjectRepository(UserEntity)\n921: private readonly userRepo: Repository<UserEntity>;\n922: \n923: // GOOD: Using custom repository extending BaseRepository\n924: constructor(private readonly userRepository: UserRepository) {}\n925: ```\n926: \n927: ### Check Existing APIs First\n928: \n929: Before implementing ANY new endpoint, grep the codebase:\n930: \n931: ```bash\n932: grep -r \"endpoint-name\\|similar-functionality\" backend/src/modules/\n933: ```\n934: \n935: Prevent duplicate functionality across modules.\n936: \n937: ---\n938: \n939: **Related Files:**\n940: \n941: - [SKILL.md](../SKILL.md) - Main guide\n942: - [architecture-overview.md](architecture-overview.md) - Four-layer architecture\n943: - [routing-and-controllers.md](routing-and-controllers.md) - Controller patterns\n944: - [database-patterns.md](database-patterns.md) - TypeORM repositories\n945: - [testing-guide.md](testing-guide.md) - Testing strategies\n\n(End of file - total 945 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Services and Repositories - NestJS Business Logic Layer\n\nComplete guide to organizing business logic with BaseService and data access with BaseRepository in NestJS.\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n- [Service Layer Overview](#service-layer-overview)\n- [BaseService Pattern](#baseservice-pattern)\n- [Repository Pattern](#repository-pattern)\n- [Dependency Injection](#dependency-injection)\n- [Service Design Principles](#service-design-principles)\n- [Testing Services](#testing-services)\n\n---\n\n## Service Layer Overview\n\n### Purpose of Services\n\n**Services contain business logic** - the 'what' and 'why' of your application:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/nestjs/guides/services-and-repositories.md","time":{"start":1779187315508,"end":1779187315818}},"id":"prt_e3fd3edf6001h2zMeMtnNIWRir","sessionID":"ses_1c02c8023ffenJEyiMDWsaqbGv","messageID":"msg_e3fd384c2001epneAUIDsTOGpZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779187317601,"sessionID":"ses_1c02c8023ffenJEyiMDWsaqbGv","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_05_kzv2MxsSN3UQiG9GADxe6871","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/validation-patterns.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/validation-patterns.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Validation Patterns - class-validator in NestJS\n2: \n3: Complete guide to input validation using class-validator and DTOs in NestJS applications.\n4: \n5: ## Table of Contents\n6: \n7: - [Validation Overview](#validation-overview)\n8: - [class-validator Decorators](#class-validator-decorators)\n9: - [DTO Patterns](#dto-patterns)\n10: - [Global ValidationPipe](#global-validationpipe)\n11: - [Custom Validators](#custom-validators)\n12: - [Swagger Integration](#swagger-integration)\n13: - [Common Validation Patterns](#common-validation-patterns)\n14: \n15: ---\n16: \n17: ## Validation Overview\n18: \n19: ### Why class-validator?\n20: \n21: NestJS uses **class-validator** with **class-transformer** for validation:\n22: \n23: **Benefits:**\n24: \n25: - ✅ **Decorator-based** - Clean, declarative syntax\n26: - ✅ **Type-safe** - Works with TypeScript classes\n27: - ✅ **Automatic** - ValidationPipe handles everything\n28: - ✅ **Swagger integration** - Auto-generates API docs\n29: - ✅ **Comprehensive** - 100+ built-in validators\n30: - ✅ **Custom validators** - Easy to extend\n31: \n32: ### Validation Flow\n33: \n34: ```\n35: 1. HTTP Request → Controller endpoint\n36: 2. ValidationPipe intercepts @Body(), @Query(), @Param()\n37: 3. class-transformer transforms plain object to class instance\n38: 4. class-validator validates decorators\n39: 5. If valid → Continue to controller\n40:    If invalid → Throw BadRequestException automatically\n41: ```\n42: \n43: ---\n44: \n45: ## class-validator Decorators\n46: \n47: ### String Validators\n48: \n49: ```typescript\n50: import {\n51:     IsString,\n52:     IsEmail,\n53:     IsUrl,\n54:     IsUUID,\n55:     MinLength,\n56:     MaxLength,\n57:     Matches,\n58:     IsNotEmpty,\n59:     IsOptional,\n60: } from 'class-validator';\n61: \n62: export class CreateUserDto {\n63:     @IsEmail({}, { message: 'Invalid email format' })\n64:     @IsNotEmpty({ message: 'Email is required' })\n65:     email: string;\n66: \n67:     @IsString()\n68:     @MinLength(2, { message: 'Name must be at least 2 characters' })\n69:     @MaxLength(100, { message: 'Name must not exceed 100 characters' })\n70:     name: string;\n71: \n72:     @IsString()\n73:     @MinLength(8, { message: 'Password must be at least 8 characters' })\n74:     @Matches(/^(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*\\d)/, {\n75:         message: 'Password must contain uppercase, lowercase, and number',\n76:     })\n77:     password: string;\n78: \n79:     @IsUrl({}, { message: 'Invalid URL format' })\n80:     @IsOptional() // Field is optional\n81:     website?: string;\n82: \n83:     @IsUUID('4', { message: 'Invalid UUID format' })\n84:     @IsOptional()\n85:     referrerId?: string;\n86: }\n87: ```\n88: \n89: ### Number Validators\n90: \n91: ```typescript\n92: import {\n93:     IsNumber,\n94:     IsInt,\n95:     IsPositive,\n96:     Min,\n97:     Max,\n98:     IsDecimal,\n99: } from 'class-validator';\n100: \n101: export class CreateProductDto {\n102:     @IsNumber({}, { message: 'Price must be a number' })\n103:     @IsPositive({ message: 'Price must be positive' })\n104:     @Min(0.01, { message: 'Price must be at least 0.01' })\n105:     @Max(999999, { message: 'Price must not exceed 999999' })\n106:     price: number;\n107: \n108:     @IsInt({ message: 'Stock must be an integer' })\n109:     @Min(0, { message: 'Stock cannot be negative' })\n110:     stock: number;\n111: \n112:     @IsDecimal(\n113:         { decimal_digits: '2' },\n114:         { message: 'Discount must have 2 decimal places' },\n115:     )\n116:     @IsOptional()\n117:     discount?: number;\n118: }\n119: ```\n120: \n121: ### Boolean Validators\n122: \n123: ```typescript\n124: import { IsBoolean } from 'class-validator';\n125: \n126: export class UpdateUserDto {\n127:     @IsBoolean({ message: 'isActive must be a boolean' })\n128:     @IsOptional()\n129:     isActive?: boolean;\n130: \n131:     @IsBoolean()\n132:     @IsOptional()\n133:     emailVerified?: boolean;\n134: }\n135: ```\n136: \n137: ### Date Validators\n138: \n139: ```typescript\n140: import { IsDate, MinDate, MaxDate } from 'class-validator';\n141: import { Type } from 'class-transformer';\n142: \n143: export class CreateEventDto {\n144:     @IsDate({ message: 'Start date must be a valid date' })\n145:     @Type(() => Date) // Transform string to Date\n146:     startDate: Date;\n147: \n148:     @IsDate()\n149:     @MinDate(new Date(), { message: 'End date must be in the future' })\n150:     @Type(() => Date)\n151:     endDate: Date;\n152: }\n153: ```\n154: \n155: ### Array Validators\n156: \n157: ```typescript\n158: import {\n159:     IsArray,\n160:     ArrayMinSize,\n161:     ArrayMaxSize,\n162:     ArrayNotEmpty,\n163:     IsString,\n164:     IsIn,\n165: } from 'class-validator';\n166: \n167: export class CreateUserDto {\n168:     @IsArray({ message: 'Roles must be an array' })\n169:     @ArrayNotEmpty({ message: 'At least one role is required' })\n170:     @ArrayMinSize(1)\n171:     @ArrayMaxSize(5)\n172:     @IsString({ each: true, message: 'Each role must be a string' })\n173:     @IsIn(['user', 'admin', 'operations'], {\n174:         each: true,\n175:         message: 'Invalid role',\n176:     })\n177:     roles: string[];\n178: \n179:     @IsArray()\n180:     @IsString({ each: true })\n181:     @IsOptional()\n182:     tags?: string[];\n183: }\n184: ```\n185: \n186: ### Enum Validators\n187: \n188: ```typescript\n189: import { IsEnum } from 'class-validator';\n190: \n191: enum UserRole {\n192:     USER = 'user',\n193:     ADMIN = 'admin',\n194:     OPERATIONS = 'operations',\n195: }\n196: \n197: enum OrderStatus {\n198:     PENDING = 'pending',\n199:     PROCESSING = 'processing',\n200:     COMPLETED = 'completed',\n201:     CANCELLED = 'cancelled',\n202: }\n203: \n204: export class CreateUserDto {\n205:     @IsEnum(UserRole, { message: 'Invalid role' })\n206:     role: UserRole;\n207: }\n208: \n209: export class UpdateOrderDto {\n210:     @IsEnum(OrderStatus, { message: 'Invalid order status' })\n211:     status: OrderStatus;\n212: }\n213: ```\n214: \n215: ### Nested Object Validators\n216: \n217: ```typescript\n218: import { ValidateNested, IsObject } from 'class-validator';\n219: import { Type } from 'class-transformer';\n220: \n221: class AddressDto {\n222:     @IsString()\n223:     @IsNotEmpty()\n224:     street: string;\n225: \n226:     @IsString()\n227:     @IsNotEmpty()\n228:     city: string;\n229: \n230:     @IsString()\n231:     @MinLength(5)\n232:     @MaxLength(10)\n233:     zipCode: string;\n234: }\n235: \n236: export class CreateUserDto {\n237:     @IsString()\n238:     name: string;\n239: \n240:     @ValidateNested()\n241:     @Type(() => AddressDto)\n242:     @IsOptional()\n243:     address?: AddressDto;\n244: }\n245: ```\n246: \n247: ---\n248: \n249: ## DTO Patterns\n250: \n251: ### Create DTO\n252: \n253: ```typescript\n254: // src/modules/users/dtos/create-user.dto.ts\n255: import {\n256:     IsEmail,\n257:     IsString,\n258:     MinLength,\n259:     MaxLength,\n260:     IsArray,\n261:     IsOptional,\n262: } from 'class-validator';\n263: import { ApiProperty } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n264: \n265: export class CreateUserDto {\n266:     @ApiProperty({\n267:         example: 'user@example.com',\n268:         description: 'User email address',\n269:     })\n270:     @IsEmail({}, { message: 'Invalid email format' })\n271:     @IsNotEmpty()\n272:     email: string;\n273: \n274:     @ApiProperty({\n275:         example: 'John Doe',\n276:         description: 'User full name',\n277:         minLength: 2,\n278:         maxLength: 100,\n279:     })\n280:     @IsString()\n281:     @MinLength(2)\n282:     @MaxLength(100)\n283:     name: string;\n284: \n285:     @ApiProperty({\n286:         example: 'SecurePassword123',\n287:         description: 'User password (min 8 characters)',\n288:         minLength: 8,\n289:     })\n290:     @IsString()\n291:     @MinLength(8)\n292:     password: string;\n293: \n294:     @ApiProperty({\n295:         example: ['user'],\n296:         description: 'User roles',\n297:         type: [String],\n298:         default: ['user'],\n299:     })\n300:     @IsArray()\n301:     @IsString({ each: true })\n302:     @IsOptional()\n303:     roles?: string[];\n304: }\n305: ```\n306: \n307: ### Update DTO with PartialType\n308: \n309: ```typescript\n310: // src/modules/users/dtos/update-user.dto.ts\n311: import { PartialType } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n312: import { CreateUserDto } from './create-user.dto';\n313: import { OmitType } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n314: \n315: // Makes all fields optional\n316: export class UpdateUserDto extends PartialType(CreateUserDto) {}\n317: \n318: // Or exclude specific fields:\n319: export class UpdateUserDto extends PartialType(\n320:     OmitType(CreateUserDto, ['email', 'password'] as const),\n321: ) {}\n322: ```\n323: \n324: ### Query DTO for Filtering\n325: \n326: ```typescript\n327: // src/shared/dtos/pagination.dto.ts\n328: import { IsInt, Min, Max, IsOptional, IsString, IsIn } from 'class-validator';\n329: import { Type } from 'class-transformer';\n330: import { ApiProperty } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n331: \n332: export class PaginationDto {\n333:     @ApiProperty({\n334:         required: false,\n335:         default: 1,\n336:         minimum: 1,\n337:     })\n338:     @Type(() => Number)\n339:     @IsInt()\n340:     @Min(1)\n341:     @IsOptional()\n342:     page?: number = 1;\n343: \n344:     @ApiProperty({\n345:         required: false,\n346:         default: 10,\n347:         minimum: 1,\n348:         maximum: 100,\n349:     })\n350:     @Type(() => Number)\n351:     @IsInt()\n352:     @Min(1)\n353:     @Max(100)\n354:     @IsOptional()\n355:     limit?: number = 10;\n356: \n357:     @ApiProperty({\n358:         required: false,\n359:         example: 'name',\n360:     })\n361:     @IsString()\n362:     @IsOptional()\n363:     sortBy?: string;\n364: \n365:     @ApiProperty({\n366:         required: false,\n367:         enum: ['ASC', 'DESC'],\n368:         default: 'ASC',\n369:     })\n370:     @IsIn(['ASC', 'DESC'])\n371:     @IsOptional()\n372:     order?: 'ASC' | 'DESC' = 'ASC';\n373: }\n374: ```\n375: \n376: ### Response DTO\n377: \n378: ```typescript\n379: // src/modules/users/dtos/user-response.dto.ts\n380: import { Exclude, Expose } from 'class-transformer';\n381: \n382: export class UserResponseDto {\n383:     @Expose()\n384:     id: string;\n385: \n386:     @Expose()\n387:     email: string;\n388: \n389:     @Expose()\n390:     name: string;\n391: \n392:     @Exclude() // Never expose password in response\n393:     password: string;\n394: \n395:     @Expose()\n396:     roles: string[];\n397: \n398:     @Expose()\n399:     createdAt: Date;\n400: \n401:     @Expose()\n402:     updatedAt: Date;\n403: }\n404: ```\n405: \n406: ---\n407: \n408: ## Global ValidationPipe\n409: \n410: ### Configuration in main.ts\n411: \n412: ```typescript\n413: // src/main.ts\n414: import { NestFactory } from '@nestjs/core';\n415: import { ValidationPipe } from '@nestjs/common';\n416: import { AppModule } from './app.module';\n417: \n418: async function bootstrap() {\n419:     const app = await NestFactory.create(AppModule);\n420: \n421:     // Global ValidationPipe\n422:     app.useGlobalPipes(\n423:         new ValidationPipe({\n424:             whitelist: true, // Strip non-DTO properties\n425:             forbidNonWhitelisted: true, // Throw error on extra properties\n426:             transform: true, // Auto-transform to DTO class\n427:             transformOptions: {\n428:                 enableImplicitConversion: true, // Convert types automatically\n429:             },\n430:             disableErrorMessages: false, // Keep error messages in production\n431:         }),\n432:     );\n433: \n434:     await app.listen(4000);\n435: }\n436: bootstrap();\n437: ```\n438: \n439: ### ValidationPipe Options Explained\n440: \n441: ```typescript\n442: {\n443:     // Remove properties not defined in DTO\n444:     whitelist: true,\n445: \n446:     // Throw error if extra properties sent\n447:     forbidNonWhitelisted: true,\n448: \n449:     // Auto-transform plain objects to DTO instances\n450:     transform: true,\n451: \n452:     // Auto-convert types (string \"123\" → number 123)\n453:     transformOptions: {\n454:         enableImplicitConversion: true,\n455:     },\n456: \n457:     // Show validation errors (even in production)\n458:     disableErrorMessages: false,\n459: \n460:     // Stop at first error (vs validate all)\n461:     stopAtFirstError: false,\n462: \n463:     // Skip missing properties validation\n464:     skipMissingProperties: false,\n465: }\n466: ```\n467: \n468: ---\n469: \n470: ## Custom Validators\n471: \n472: ### Custom Decorator Example\n473: \n474: ```typescript\n475: // src/core/validators/is-strong-password.validator.ts\n476: import {\n477:     registerDecorator,\n478:     ValidationOptions,\n479:     ValidatorConstraint,\n480:     ValidatorConstraintInterface,\n481: } from 'class-validator';\n482: \n483: @ValidatorConstraint({ async: false })\n484: export class IsStrongPasswordConstraint\n485:     implements ValidatorConstraintInterface\n486: {\n487:     validate(password: string): boolean {\n488:         // At least 8 characters, 1 uppercase, 1 lowercase, 1 number, 1 special char\n489:         const strongPasswordRegex =\n490:             /^(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*\\d)(?=.*[@$!%*?&])[A-Za-z\\d@$!%*?&]{8,}$/;\n491:         return strongPasswordRegex.test(password);\n492:     }\n493: \n494:     defaultMessage(): string {\n495:         return 'Password must be at least 8 characters with uppercase, lowercase, number, and special character';\n496:     }\n497: }\n498: \n499: export function IsStrongPassword(validationOptions?: ValidationOptions) {\n500:     return function (object: Object, propertyName: string) {\n501:         registerDecorator({\n502:             target: object.constructor,\n503:             propertyName: propertyName,\n504:             options: validationOptions,\n505:             constraints: [],\n506:             validator: IsStrongPasswordConstraint,\n507:         });\n508:     };\n509: }\n510: \n511: // Usage:\n512: export class CreateUserDto {\n513:     @IsStrongPassword()\n514:     password: string;\n515: }\n516: ```\n517: \n518: ### Async Custom Validator (Check Database)\n519: \n520: ```typescript\n521: // src/modules/users/validators/is-email-unique.validator.ts\n522: import { Injectable } from '@nestjs/common';\n523: import {\n524:     registerDecorator,\n525:     ValidationOptions,\n526:     ValidatorConstraint,\n527:     ValidatorConstraintInterface,\n528:     ValidationArguments,\n529: } from 'class-validator';\n530: import { UserRepository } from '../user.repository';\n531: \n532: @ValidatorConstraint({ async: true })\n533: @Injectable()\n534: export class IsEmailUniqueConstraint implements ValidatorConstraintInterface {\n535:     constructor(private readonly userRepository: UserRepository) {}\n536: \n537:     async validate(email: string, args: ValidationArguments): Promise<boolean> {\n538:         const user = await this.userRepository.findOne({ where: { email } });\n539:         return !user; // Return true if email doesn't exist\n540:     }\n541: \n542:     defaultMessage(): string {\n543:         return 'Email $value already exists';\n544:     }\n545: }\n546: \n547: export function IsEmailUnique(validationOptions?: ValidationOptions) {\n548:     return function (object: Object, propertyName: string) {\n549:         registerDecorator({\n550:             target: object.constructor,\n551:             propertyName: propertyName,\n552:             options: validationOptions,\n553:             constraints: [],\n554:             validator: IsEmailUniqueConstraint,\n555:         });\n556:     };\n557: }\n558: \n559: // Usage:\n560: export class CreateUserDto {\n561:     @IsEmail()\n562:     @IsEmailUnique() // Checks database\n563:     email: string;\n564: }\n565: \n566: // Register in module:\n567: @Module({\n568:     providers: [IsEmailUniqueConstraint],\n569: })\n570: export class UserModule {}\n571: ```\n572: \n573: ### Conditional Validation\n574: \n575: ```typescript\n576: import { ValidateIf } from 'class-validator';\n577: \n578: export class CreateOrderDto {\n579:     @IsEnum(PaymentMethod)\n580:     paymentMethod: PaymentMethod;\n581: \n582:     // Only validate if paymentMethod is 'credit_card'\n583:     @ValidateIf((o) => o.paymentMethod === 'credit_card')\n584:     @IsString()\n585:     @MinLength(16)\n586:     @MaxLength(16)\n587:     cardNumber?: string;\n588: \n589:     @ValidateIf((o) => o.paymentMethod === 'credit_card')\n590:     @IsString()\n591:     @Matches(/^(0[1-9]|1[0-2])\\/\\d{2}$/)\n592:     expiryDate?: string;\n593: }\n594: ```\n595: \n596: ---\n597: \n598: ## Swagger Integration\n599: \n600: ### Complete DTO with Swagger\n601: \n602: ```typescript\n603: import { ApiProperty, ApiPropertyOptional } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n604: import {\n605:     IsEmail,\n606:     IsString,\n607:     MinLength,\n608:     IsOptional,\n609:     IsArray,\n610: } from 'class-validator';\n611: \n612: export class CreateUserDto {\n613:     @ApiProperty({\n614:         description: 'User email address',\n615:         example: 'user@example.com',\n616:         format: 'email',\n617:     })\n618:     @IsEmail({}, { message: 'Invalid email format' })\n619:     email: string;\n620: \n621:     @ApiProperty({\n622:         description: 'User full name',\n623:         example: 'John Doe',\n624:         minLength: 2,\n625:         maxLength: 100,\n626:     })\n627:     @IsString()\n628:     @MinLength(2)\n629:     @MaxLength(100)\n630:     name: string;\n631: \n632:     @ApiProperty({\n633:         description: 'User password',\n634:         example: 'SecurePassword123',\n635:         minLength: 8,\n636:         format: 'password',\n637:     })\n638:     @IsString()\n639:     @MinLength(8)\n640:     password: string;\n641: \n642:     @ApiPropertyOptional({\n643:         description: 'User roles',\n644:         example: ['user'],\n645:         type: [String],\n646:         default: ['user'],\n647:     })\n648:     @IsArray()\n649:     @IsString({ each: true })\n650:     @IsOptional()\n651:     roles?: string[];\n652: }\n653: ```\n654: \n655: ---\n656: \n657: ## Common Validation Patterns\n658: \n659: ### Email Validation\n660: \n661: ```typescript\n662: @IsEmail({}, { message: 'Invalid email format' })\n663: @IsNotEmpty()\n664: email: string;\n665: ```\n666: \n667: ### Password Validation\n668: \n669: ```typescript\n670: @IsString()\n671: @MinLength(8, { message: 'Password must be at least 8 characters' })\n672: @Matches(/^(?=.*[a-z])(?=.*[A-Z])(?=.*\\d)/, {\n673:     message: 'Password must contain uppercase, lowercase, and number',\n674: })\n675: password: string;\n676: ```\n677: \n678: ### UUID Validation\n679: \n680: ```typescript\n681: @IsUUID('4', { message: 'Invalid UUID format' })\n682: id: string;\n683: ```\n684: \n685: ### Phone Number Validation\n686: \n687: ```typescript\n688: @IsString()\n689: @Matches(/^\\+?[1-9]\\d{1,14}$/, {\n690:     message: 'Invalid phone number format (E.164)',\n691: })\n692: @IsOptional()\n693: phone?: string;\n694: ```\n695: \n696: ### URL Validation\n697: \n698: ```typescript\n699: @IsUrl({}, { message: 'Invalid URL format' })\n700: @IsOptional()\n701: website?: string;\n702: ```\n703: \n704: ### Date Range Validation\n705: \n706: ```typescript\n707: @IsDate()\n708: @Type(() => Date)\n709: @MinDate(new Date(), { message: 'Start date must be in the future' })\n710: startDate: Date;\n711: \n712: @IsDate()\n713: @Type(() => Date)\n714: @MinDate(new Date(), { message: 'End date must be after start date' })\n715: endDate: Date;\n716: ```\n717: \n718: ### File Upload Validation\n719: \n720: ```typescript\n721: import { IsNotEmpty, IsString, IsMimeType } from 'class-validator';\n722: \n723: export class FileUploadDto {\n724:     @IsString()\n725:     @IsNotEmpty()\n726:     filename: string;\n727: \n728:     @IsString()\n729:     @IsMimeType({ message: 'Invalid file type' })\n730:     mimetype: string;\n731: \n732:     @IsNumber()\n733:     @Max(5242880, { message: 'File size must not exceed 5MB' })\n734:     size: number;\n735: }\n736: ```\n737: \n738: ---\n739: \n740: ## Validation Error Response\n741: \n742: When validation fails, NestJS automatically returns:\n743: \n744: ```json\n745: {\n746:     \"success\": false,\n747:     \"statusCode\": 400,\n748:     \"message\": \"Validation failed\",\n749:     \"errors\": [\n750:         {\n751:             \"field\": \"email\",\n752:             \"constraints\": {\n753:                 \"isEmail\": \"Invalid email format\",\n754:                 \"isNotEmpty\": \"Email is required\"\n755:             }\n756:         },\n757:         {\n758:             \"field\": \"password\",\n759:             \"constraints\": {\n760:                 \"minLength\": \"Password must be at least 8 characters\"\n761:             }\n762:         }\n763:     ],\n764:     \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-01T12:00:00.000Z\",\n765:     \"path\": \"/api/users\"\n766: }\n767: ```\n768: \n769: ---\n770: \n771: ## Best Practices Summary\n772: \n773: ### ✅ DO:\n774: \n775: - Use class-validator decorators on all DTOs\n776: - Enable global ValidationPipe with whitelist\n777: - Provide custom error messages\n778: - Use @ApiProperty for Swagger documentation\n779: - Create separate DTOs for create/update/response\n780: - Use PartialType for update DTOs\n781: - Transform types with @Type() decorator\n782: - Validate nested objects with @ValidateNested\n783: - Use @IsOptional for optional fields\n784: - Create custom validators for complex rules\n785: \n786: ### ❌ DON'T:\n787: \n788: - Skip validation on user input\n789: - Use plain objects instead of class DTOs\n790: - Forget to enable transform: true\n791: - Mix validation logic in services\n792: - Expose sensitive fields in response DTOs\n793: - Use any type\n794: - Skip Swagger decorators\n795: - Forget @Type() for dates and nested objects\n796: - Allow arbitrary extra properties (use whitelist)\n797: - Write validation logic in controllers\n798: \n799: ---\n800: \n801: ---\n802: \n803: ## MANDATORY: I18nHelper for Validation Messages\n804: \n805: Custom validation messages MUST use I18nHelper, not hardcoded strings:\n806: \n807: ```typescript\n808: // BAD\n809: @IsEmail({}, { message: 'Invalid email format' })\n810: \n811: // GOOD\n812: @IsEmail({}, { message: I18nHelper.t('validation.invalidEmail') })\n813: ```\n814: \n815: For standard class-validator decorators, the default messages are acceptable. But any custom `message` property MUST go through I18nHelper.\n816: \n817: ## MANDATORY: DTO Naming & Organization\n818: \n819: - Create DTOs in `src/modules/[module]/dto/`\n820: - Naming: `Create[Entity]Dto`, `Update[Entity]Dto`, `[Entity]ResponseDto`, `[Entity]QueryDto`\n821: - Use `PartialType(CreateXxxDto)` for update DTOs (not duplicating fields)\n822: - Use `PickType` / `OmitType` for derived DTOs\n823: - Swagger `@ApiProperty()` on EVERY field — no exceptions\n824: - `@ApiPropertyOptional()` for optional fields\n825: \n826: ---\n827: \n828: **Related Files:**\n829: \n830: - [SKILL.md](../SKILL.md) - Main guide\n831: - [routing-and-controllers.md](routing-and-controllers.md) - DTO usage in controllers\n832: - [services-and-repositories.md](services-and-repositories.md) - Service layer\n833: - [database-patterns.md](database-patterns.md) - Entity validation\n\n(End of file - total 833 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Validation Patterns - class-validator in NestJS\n\nComplete guide to input validation using class-validator and DTOs in NestJS applications.\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n- [Validation Overview](#validation-overview)\n- [class-validator Decorators](#class-validator-decorators)\n- [DTO Patterns](#dto-patterns)\n- [Global ValidationPipe](#global-validationpipe)\n- [Custom Validators](#custom-validators)\n- [Swagger Integration](#swagger-integration)\n- [Common Validation Patterns](#common-validation-patterns)\n\n---\n\n## Validation Overview\n\n### Why class-validator?\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/nestjs/guides/validation-patterns.md","time":{"start":1779187317290,"end":1779187317600}},"id":"prt_e3fd3f4c2001zJl2RjXpUvHb8F","sessionID":"ses_1c02c8023ffenJEyiMDWsaqbGv","messageID":"msg_e3fd384c2001epneAUIDsTOGpZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779187319374,"sessionID":"ses_1c02c8023ffenJEyiMDWsaqbGv","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_06_TyXpZYan7XdLVSSIAXEg9064","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/database-patterns.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude/nestjs/guides/database-patterns.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Database Patterns - TypeORM in NestJS\n2: \n3: Complete guide to database access patterns using TypeORM with PostgreSQL in NestJS applications.\n4: \n5: ## Table of Contents\n6: \n7: - [TypeORM Fundamentals](#typeorm-fundamentals)\n8: - [Entity Patterns](#entity-patterns)\n9: - [Repository Pattern](#repository-pattern)\n10: - [Relationships](#relationships)\n11: - [Migrations](#migrations)\n12: - [Query Optimization](#query-optimization)\n13: - [Transactions](#transactions)\n14: - [Error Handling](#error-handling)\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## TypeORM Fundamentals\n19: \n20: ### BaseEntity Pattern\n21: \n22: All entities should extend BaseEntity for automatic timestamps and soft delete:\n23: \n24: ```typescript\n25: // src/core/base/base.entity.ts\n26: import {\n27:     PrimaryGeneratedColumn,\n28:     CreateDateColumn,\n29:     UpdateDateColumn,\n30:     DeleteDateColumn,\n31: } from 'typeorm';\n32: \n33: export abstract class BaseEntity {\n34:     @PrimaryGeneratedColumn('uuid')\n35:     id: string;\n36: \n37:     @CreateDateColumn({ type: 'timestamp' })\n38:     createdAt: Date;\n39: \n40:     @UpdateDateColumn({ type: 'timestamp' })\n41:     updatedAt: Date;\n42: \n43:     @DeleteDateColumn({ type: 'timestamp', nullable: true })\n44:     deletedAt: Date | null;\n45: }\n46: ```\n47: \n48: ### Database Configuration\n49: \n50: ```typescript\n51: // src/config/db.config.ts\n52: import { TypeOrmModuleOptions } from '@nestjs/typeorm';\n53: import { envConfigService } from './env-config.service';\n54: \n55: export const dbConfig: TypeOrmModuleOptions = {\n56:     type: 'postgres',\n57:     host: envConfigService.get('DB_HOST'),\n58:     port: envConfigService.get('DB_PORT'),\n59:     username: envConfigService.get('DB_USERNAME'),\n60:     password: envConfigService.get('DB_PASSWORD'),\n61:     database: envConfigService.get('DB_DATABASE'),\n62:     entities: [__dirname + '/../**/*.entity{.ts,.js}'],\n63:     migrations: [__dirname + '/../database/migrations/*{.ts,.js}'],\n64:     synchronize: false, // NEVER true in production\n65:     logging: envConfigService.get('NODE_ENV') === 'development',\n66:     ssl:\n67:         envConfigService.get('NODE_ENV') === 'production'\n68:             ? {\n69:                   rejectUnauthorized: false,\n70:               }\n71:             : false,\n72: };\n73: ```\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## Entity Patterns\n78: \n79: ### Basic Entity\n80: \n81: ```typescript\n82: // src/modules/users/user.entity.ts\n83: import { Entity, Column } from 'typeorm';\n84: import { BaseEntity } from 'src/core/base';\n85: \n86: @Entity('users')\n87: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n88:     @Column({ unique: true })\n89:     email: string;\n90: \n91:     @Column()\n92:     name: string;\n93: \n94:     @Column()\n95:     password: string;\n96: \n97:     @Column({ default: true })\n98:     isActive: boolean;\n99: \n100:     @Column('simple-array', { default: [] })\n101:     roles: string[];\n102: }\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ### Column Types\n106: \n107: ```typescript\n108: import { Entity, Column } from 'typeorm';\n109: import { BaseEntity } from 'src/core/base';\n110: \n111: @Entity('products')\n112: export class Product extends BaseEntity {\n113:     // String columns\n114:     @Column({ type: 'varchar', length: 255 })\n115:     name: string;\n116: \n117:     @Column({ type: 'text', nullable: true })\n118:     description: string | null;\n119: \n120:     // Number columns\n121:     @Column({ type: 'decimal', precision: 10, scale: 2 })\n122:     price: number;\n123: \n124:     @Column({ type: 'int', default: 0 })\n125:     stock: number;\n126: \n127:     // Boolean\n128:     @Column({ type: 'boolean', default: true })\n129:     isAvailable: boolean;\n130: \n131:     // Date/Time\n132:     @Column({ type: 'timestamp', nullable: true })\n133:     publishedAt: Date | null;\n134: \n135:     // JSON\n136:     @Column({ type: 'jsonb', nullable: true })\n137:     metadata: Record<string, any> | null;\n138: \n139:     // Array (PostgreSQL)\n140:     @Column('simple-array')\n141:     tags: string[];\n142: \n143:     // Enum (MUST use shared enum from src/shared/enums/, NEVER use varchar for enum columns)\n144:     @Column({\n145:         type: 'enum',\n146:         enum: StatusEnum,\n147:         default: StatusEnum.PENDING,\n148:     })\n149:     status: StatusEnum;\n150: }\n151: ```\n152: \n153: ### Index and Unique Constraints\n154: \n155: ```typescript\n156: import { Entity, Column, Index, Unique } from 'typeorm';\n157: import { BaseEntity } from 'src/core/base';\n158: \n159: @Entity('users')\n160: @Unique(['email'])\n161: @Index(['email', 'isActive']) // Composite index\n162: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n163:     @Column({ unique: true })\n164:     @Index()\n165:     email: string;\n166: \n167:     @Column()\n168:     @Index()\n169:     name: string;\n170: \n171:     @Column()\n172:     password: string;\n173: \n174:     @Column({ default: true })\n175:     isActive: boolean;\n176: }\n177: ```\n178: \n179: ---\n180: \n181: ## Repository Pattern\n182: \n183: ### BaseRepository Implementation\n184: \n185: ```typescript\n186: // src/core/base/base.repository.ts\n187: import {\n188:     Repository,\n189:     FindManyOptions,\n190:     FindOneOptions,\n191:     DeepPartial,\n192: } from 'typeorm';\n193: import { BaseEntity } from './base.entity';\n194: \n195: export abstract class BaseRepository<T extends BaseEntity> {\n196:     constructor(protected readonly repository: Repository<T>) {}\n197: \n198:     async findAll(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<T[]> {\n199:         return this.repository.find(options);\n200:     }\n201: \n202:     async findById(id: string, relations?: string[]): Promise<T | null> {\n203:         return this.repository.findOne({\n204:             where: { id } as any,\n205:             relations,\n206:         });\n207:     }\n208: \n209:     async findOne(options: FindOneOptions<T>): Promise<T | null> {\n210:         return this.repository.findOne(options);\n211:     }\n212: \n213:     async create(data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T> {\n214:         const entity = this.repository.create(data);\n215:         return this.repository.save(entity);\n216:     }\n217: \n218:     async update(id: string, data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T | null> {\n219:         await this.repository.update(id, data as any);\n220:         return this.findById(id);\n221:     }\n222: \n223:     async softDelete(id: string): Promise<void> {\n224:         await this.repository.softDelete(id);\n225:     }\n226: \n227:     async delete(id: string): Promise<void> {\n228:         await this.repository.delete(id);\n229:     }\n230: \n231:     async count(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<number> {\n232:         return this.repository.count(options);\n233:     }\n234: }\n235: ```\n236: \n237: ### Custom Repository\n238: \n239: ```typescript\n240: // src/modules/users/user.repository.ts\n241: import { Injectable } from '@nestjs/common';\n242: import { InjectRepository } from '@nestjs/typeorm';\n243: import { Repository } from 'typeorm';\n244: import { BaseRepository } from 'src/core/base';\n245: import { User } from './user.entity';\n246: \n247: @Injectable()\n248: export class UserRepository extends BaseRepository<User> {\n249:     constructor(\n250:         @InjectRepository(User)\n251:         repository: Repository<User>,\n252:     ) {\n253:         super(repository);\n254:     }\n255: \n256:     // Custom queries\n257:     async findByEmail(email: string): Promise<User | null> {\n258:         return this.repository.findOne({\n259:             where: { email },\n260:         });\n261:     }\n262: \n263:     async findActiveUsers(): Promise<User[]> {\n264:         return this.repository.find({\n265:             where: { isActive: true },\n266:             order: { createdAt: 'DESC' },\n267:         });\n268:     }\n269: \n270:     async findWithRoles(userId: string): Promise<User | null> {\n271:         return this.repository\n272:             .createQueryBuilder('user')\n273:             .where('user.id = :userId', { userId })\n274:             .andWhere(\"'admin' = ANY(user.roles)\")\n275:             .getOne();\n276:     }\n277: \n278:     async searchByName(query: string): Promise<User[]> {\n279:         return this.repository\n280:             .createQueryBuilder('user')\n281:             .where('user.name ILIKE :query', { query: `%${query}%` })\n282:             .andWhere('user.isActive = :isActive', { isActive: true })\n283:             .orderBy('user.name', 'ASC')\n284:             .getMany();\n285:     }\n286: }\n287: ```\n288: \n289: ---\n290: \n291: ## Relationships\n292: \n293: ### One-to-One\n294: \n295: ```typescript\n296: // user.entity.ts\n297: import { Entity, Column, OneToOne, JoinColumn } from 'typeorm';\n298: import { BaseEntity } from 'src/core/base';\n299: import { Profile } from './profile.entity';\n300: \n301: @Entity('users')\n302: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n303:     @Column()\n304:     email: string;\n305: \n306:     @OneToOne(() => Profile, (profile) => profile.user, { cascade: true })\n307:     @JoinColumn()\n308:     profile: Profile;\n309: }\n310: \n311: // profile.entity.ts\n312: @Entity('profiles')\n313: export class Profile extends BaseEntity {\n314:     @Column()\n315:     firstName: string;\n316: \n317:     @Column()\n318:     lastName: string;\n319: \n320:     @OneToOne(() => User, (user) => user.profile)\n321:     user: User;\n322: }\n323: ```\n324: \n325: ### One-to-Many / Many-to-One\n326: \n327: ```typescript\n328: // user.entity.ts\n329: import { Entity, Column, OneToMany } from 'typeorm';\n330: import { BaseEntity } from 'src/core/base';\n331: import { Post } from '../posts/post.entity';\n332: \n333: @Entity('users')\n334: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n335:     @Column()\n336:     name: string;\n337: \n338:     @OneToMany(() => Post, (post) => post.author)\n339:     posts: Post[];\n340: }\n341: \n342: // post.entity.ts\n343: import { Entity, Column, ManyToOne, JoinColumn } from 'typeorm';\n344: import { BaseEntity } from 'src/core/base';\n345: import { User } from '../users/user.entity';\n346: \n347: @Entity('posts')\n348: export class Post extends BaseEntity {\n349:     @Column()\n350:     title: string;\n351: \n352:     @Column('text')\n353:     content: string;\n354: \n355:     @Column()\n356:     authorId: string;\n357: \n358:     @ManyToOne(() => User, (user) => user.posts)\n359:     @JoinColumn({ name: 'authorId' })\n360:     author: User;\n361: }\n362: ```\n363: \n364: ### Many-to-Many\n365: \n366: ```typescript\n367: // user.entity.ts\n368: import { Entity, Column, ManyToMany, JoinTable } from 'typeorm';\n369: import { BaseEntity } from 'src/core/base';\n370: import { Role } from '../roles/role.entity';\n371: \n372: @Entity('users')\n373: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n374:     @Column()\n375:     name: string;\n376: \n377:     @ManyToMany(() => Role, (role) => role.users)\n378:     @JoinTable({\n379:         name: 'user_roles',\n380:         joinColumn: { name: 'userId', referencedColumnName: 'id' },\n381:         inverseJoinColumn: { name: 'roleId', referencedColumnName: 'id' },\n382:     })\n383:     roles: Role[];\n384: }\n385: \n386: // role.entity.ts\n387: @Entity('roles')\n388: export class Role extends BaseEntity {\n389:     @Column({ unique: true })\n390:     name: string;\n391: \n392:     @ManyToMany(() => User, (user) => user.roles)\n393:     users: User[];\n394: }\n395: ```\n396: \n397: ### Loading Relations\n398: \n399: ```typescript\n400: // Eager loading (automatically loads relations)\n401: @Entity('users')\n402: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n403:     @OneToOne(() => Profile, (profile) => profile.user, { eager: true })\n404:     @JoinColumn()\n405:     profile: Profile;\n406: }\n407: \n408: // Lazy loading\n409: const user = await userRepository.findOne({\n410:     where: { id },\n411:     relations: ['profile', 'posts'],\n412: });\n413: \n414: // With QueryBuilder\n415: const user = await userRepository\n416:     .createQueryBuilder('user')\n417:     .leftJoinAndSelect('user.profile', 'profile')\n418:     .leftJoinAndSelect('user.posts', 'posts')\n419:     .where('user.id = :id', { id })\n420:     .getOne();\n421: \n422: // Nested relations\n423: const user = await userRepository.findOne({\n424:     where: { id },\n425:     relations: {\n426:         profile: true,\n427:         posts: {\n428:             comments: true,\n429:         },\n430:     },\n431: });\n432: ```\n433: \n434: ---\n435: \n436: ## Migrations\n437: \n438: ### Generate Migration\n439: \n440: ```bash\n441: # Generate migration from entity changes\n442: npm run migration:generate -- src/database/migrations/CreateUserTable\n443: \n444: # Create empty migration\n445: npm run migration:create -- src/database/migrations/AddIndexToUser\n446: ```\n447: \n448: ### Migration File\n449: \n450: ```typescript\n451: // src/database/migrations/1234567890-CreateUserTable.ts\n452: import { MigrationInterface, QueryRunner, Table } from 'typeorm';\n453: \n454: export class CreateUserTable1234567890 implements MigrationInterface {\n455:     public async up(queryRunner: QueryRunner): Promise<void> {\n456:         await queryRunner.createTable(\n457:             new Table({\n458:                 name: 'users',\n459:                 columns: [\n460:                     {\n461:                         name: 'id',\n462:                         type: 'uuid',\n463:                         isPrimary: true,\n464:                         generationStrategy: 'uuid',\n465:                         default: 'uuid_generate_v4()',\n466:                     },\n467:                     {\n468:                         name: 'email',\n469:                         type: 'varchar',\n470:                         length: '255',\n471:                         isUnique: true,\n472:                     },\n473:                     {\n474:                         name: 'name',\n475:                         type: 'varchar',\n476:                         length: '255',\n477:                     },\n478:                     {\n479:                         name: 'password',\n480:                         type: 'varchar',\n481:                         length: '255',\n482:                     },\n483:                     {\n484:                         name: 'isActive',\n485:                         type: 'boolean',\n486:                         default: true,\n487:                     },\n488:                     {\n489:                         name: 'roles',\n490:                         type: 'text',\n491:                         isArray: true,\n492:                         default: 'ARRAY[]::text[]',\n493:                     },\n494:                     {\n495:                         name: 'createdAt',\n496:                         type: 'timestamp',\n497:                         default: 'now()',\n498:                     },\n499:                     {\n500:                         name: 'updatedAt',\n501:                         type: 'timestamp',\n502:                         default: 'now()',\n503:                     },\n504:                     {\n505:                         name: 'deletedAt',\n506:                         type: 'timestamp',\n507:                         isNullable: true,\n508:                     },\n509:                 ],\n510:                 indices: [\n511:                     {\n512:                         name: 'IDX_USER_EMAIL',\n513:                         columnNames: ['email'],\n514:                     },\n515:                 ],\n516:             }),\n517:             true,\n518:         );\n519:     }\n520: \n521:     public async down(queryRunner: QueryRunner): Promise<void> {\n522:         await queryRunner.dropTable('users');\n523:     }\n524: }\n525: ```\n526: \n527: ### Run Migrations\n528: \n529: ```bash\n530: # Run all pending migrations\n531: npm run migration:run\n532: \n533: # Revert last migration\n534: npm run migration:revert\n535: \n536: # Show migration status\n537: npm run migration:show\n538: ```\n539: \n540: ---\n541: \n542: ## Query Optimization\n543: \n544: ### Select Specific Fields\n545: \n546: ```typescript\n547: // ❌ Fetches all fields\n548: const users = await userRepository.find();\n549: \n550: // ✅ Only fetch needed fields\n551: const users = await userRepository.find({\n552:     select: ['id', 'email', 'name'],\n553: });\n554: \n555: // With QueryBuilder\n556: const users = await userRepository\n557:     .createQueryBuilder('user')\n558:     .select(['user.id', 'user.email', 'user.name'])\n559:     .getMany();\n560: ```\n561: \n562: ### Pagination\n563: \n564: ```typescript\n565: async findPaginated(page: number = 1, limit: number = 10): Promise<[User[], number]> {\n566:     const skip = (page - 1) * limit;\n567: \n568:     return this.repository.findAndCount({\n569:         skip,\n570:         take: limit,\n571:         order: { createdAt: 'DESC' },\n572:     });\n573: }\n574: \n575: // With QueryBuilder\n576: async findPaginatedWithSearch(\n577:     page: number,\n578:     limit: number,\n579:     search?: string,\n580: ): Promise<[User[], number]> {\n581:     const query = this.repository\n582:         .createQueryBuilder('user')\n583:         .skip((page - 1) * limit)\n584:         .take(limit)\n585:         .orderBy('user.createdAt', 'DESC');\n586: \n587:     if (search) {\n588:         query.where('user.name ILIKE :search', { search: `%${search}%` });\n589:     }\n590: \n591:     return query.getManyAndCount();\n592: }\n593: ```\n594: \n595: ### N+1 Query Prevention\n596: \n597: ```typescript\n598: // ❌ N+1 Problem\n599: const users = await userRepository.find();\n600: for (const user of users) {\n601:     user.posts = await postRepository.find({ where: { authorId: user.id } });\n602: }\n603: \n604: // ✅ Solution: Use relations\n605: const users = await userRepository.find({\n606:     relations: ['posts'],\n607: });\n608: \n609: // ✅ Or use QueryBuilder with join\n610: const users = await userRepository\n611:     .createQueryBuilder('user')\n612:     .leftJoinAndSelect('user.posts', 'post')\n613:     .getMany();\n614: ```\n615: \n616: ### Indexes\n617: \n618: ```typescript\n619: // Add indexes for frequently queried fields\n620: @Entity('users')\n621: @Index(['email', 'isActive']) // Composite index\n622: export class User extends BaseEntity {\n623:     @Column({ unique: true })\n624:     @Index() // Single field index\n625:     email: string;\n626: \n627:     @Column()\n628:     @Index()\n629:     name: string;\n630: \n631:     @Column({ default: true })\n632:     isActive: boolean;\n633: }\n634: ```\n635: \n636: ---\n637: \n638: ## Transactions\n639: \n640: ### Simple Transaction\n641: \n642: ```typescript\n643: import { DataSource } from 'typeorm';\n644: \n645: @Injectable()\n646: export class UserService {\n647:     constructor(private dataSource: DataSource) {}\n648: \n649:     async createUserWithProfile(userData: CreateUserDto): Promise<User> {\n650:         const queryRunner = this.dataSource.createQueryRunner();\n651:         await queryRunner.connect();\n652:         await queryRunner.startTransaction();\n653: \n654:         try {\n655:             // Create user\n656:             const user = queryRunner.manager.create(User, userData);\n657:             await queryRunner.manager.save(user);\n658: \n659:             // Create profile\n660:             const profile = queryRunner.manager.create(Profile, {\n661:                 userId: user.id,\n662:                 firstName: userData.firstName,\n663:                 lastName: userData.lastName,\n664:             });\n665:             await queryRunner.manager.save(profile);\n666: \n667:             // Commit transaction\n668:             await queryRunner.commitTransaction();\n669:             return user;\n670:         } catch (error) {\n671:             // Rollback on error\n672:             await queryRunner.rollbackTransaction();\n673:             throw error;\n674:         } finally {\n675:             // Release query runner\n676:             await queryRunner.release();\n677:         }\n678:     }\n679: }\n680: ```\n681: \n682: ### Transaction with DataSource\n683: \n684: ```typescript\n685: async transferFunds(fromId: string, toId: string, amount: number): Promise<void> {\n686:     await this.dataSource.transaction(async (manager) => {\n687:         // Deduct from sender\n688:         await manager.decrement(\n689:             Account,\n690:             { id: fromId },\n691:             'balance',\n692:             amount,\n693:         );\n694: \n695:         // Add to receiver\n696:         await manager.increment(\n697:             Account,\n698:             { id: toId },\n699:             'balance',\n700:             amount,\n701:         );\n702: \n703:         // Create transfer record\n704:         await manager.save(TransferLog, {\n705:             fromId,\n706:             toId,\n707:             amount,\n708:         });\n709:     });\n710: }\n711: ```\n712: \n713: ---\n714: \n715: ## Error Handling\n716: \n717: ### TypeORM Errors\n718: \n719: ```typescript\n720: import { QueryFailedError } from 'typeorm';\n721: import { ConflictException, NotFoundException, BadRequestException } from '@nestjs/common';\n722: \n723: async createUser(data: CreateUserDto): Promise<User> {\n724:     try {\n725:         return await this.repository.create(data);\n726:     } catch (error) {\n727:         if (error instanceof QueryFailedError) {\n728:             // Unique constraint violation\n729:             if (error.message.includes('duplicate key')) {\n730:                 throw new ConflictException('Email already exists');\n731:             }\n732: \n733:             // Foreign key constraint\n734:             if (error.message.includes('foreign key constraint')) {\n735:                 throw new BadRequestException('Invalid reference');\n736:             }\n737: \n738:             // Not null constraint\n739:             if (error.message.includes('not-null constraint')) {\n740:                 throw new BadRequestException('Required field missing');\n741:             }\n742:         }\n743: \n744:         throw error;\n745:     }\n746: }\n747: ```\n748: \n749: ### Custom Error Handler\n750: \n751: ```typescript\n752: @Injectable()\n753: export class DatabaseErrorHandler {\n754:     handleError(error: unknown): never {\n755:         if (error instanceof QueryFailedError) {\n756:             const message = error.message.toLowerCase();\n757: \n758:             if (message.includes('duplicate key')) {\n759:                 throw new ConflictException('Resource already exists');\n760:             }\n761: \n762:             if (message.includes('foreign key')) {\n763:                 throw new BadRequestException('Invalid reference');\n764:             }\n765: \n766:             if (message.includes('not-null')) {\n767:                 throw new BadRequestException('Required field missing');\n768:             }\n769:         }\n770: \n771:         throw new InternalServerErrorException('Database operation failed');\n772:     }\n773: }\n774: ```\n775: \n776: ---\n777: \n778: ## Best Practices Summary\n779: \n780: ### ✅ DO:\n781: \n782: - Extend BaseEntity for all entities\n783: - Use migrations for schema changes (never synchronize in production)\n784: - Add indexes on frequently queried fields\n785: - Use transactions for multi-step operations\n786: - Select only needed fields\n787: - Use relations to prevent N+1 queries\n788: - Use QueryBuilder for complex queries\n789: - Handle database errors properly\n790: - Use soft delete for important data\n791: - Add unique constraints where needed\n792: \n793: ### ❌ DON'T:\n794: \n795: - Use synchronize: true in production\n796: - Forget to add indexes on foreign keys\n797: - Load unnecessary relations\n798: - Skip transactions for multi-step operations\n799: - Expose raw database errors to users\n800: - Use SELECT \\* in queries\n801: - Hard delete without consideration\n802: - Forget to release query runners\n803: - Use eager loading everywhere\n804: - Skip migration testing\n805: \n806: ---\n807: \n808: **Related Files:**\n809: \n810: - [SKILL.md](../SKILL.md) - Main guide\n811: - [services-and-repositories.md](services-and-repositories.md) - Service/Repository patterns\n812: - [architecture-overview.md](architecture-overview.md) - Four-layer architecture\n813: - [validation-patterns.md](validation-patterns.md) - Entity validation\n\n(End of file - total 813 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Database Patterns - TypeORM in NestJS\n\nComplete guide to database access patterns using TypeORM with PostgreSQL in NestJS applications.\n\n## Table of Contents\n\n- [TypeORM Fundamentals](#typeorm-fundamentals)\n- [Entity Patterns](#entity-patterns)\n- [Repository Pattern](#repository-pattern)\n- [Relationships](#relationships)\n- [Migrations](#migrations)\n- [Query Optimization](#query-optimization)\n- [Transactions](#transactions)\n- [Error Handling](#error-handling)\n\n---\n\n## TypeORM Fundamentals\n\n### BaseEntity Pattern","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude/nestjs/guides/database-patterns.md","time":{"start":1779187319076,"end":1779187319373}},"id":"prt_e3fd3fbb40016iySAn7i1Vyzyb","sessionID":"ses_1c02c8023ffenJEyiMDWsaqbGv","messageID":"msg_e3fd384c2001epneAUIDsTOGpZ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779187512779,"sessionID":"ses_1c02c8023ffenJEyiMDWsaqbGv","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_01_tbkFZmiZ4G4DMQ666zXQ7559","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Read base classes framework","prompt":"Read ALL of these files completely and return their full contents:\n1. backend/src/core/base/base.entity.ts\n2. backend/src/core/base/base.repository.ts\n3. backend/src/core/base/base.service.ts\n4. backend/src/core/base/base.controller.ts\n5. backend/src/core/base/index.ts\n6. backend/src/core/decorators/index.ts\n7. backend/src/core/decorators/public.decorator.ts\n8. backend/src/core/decorators/roles.decorator.ts\n9. backend/src/core/decorators/current-user.decorator.ts\n10. backend/src/core/decorators/api-swagger.decorator.ts\n11. backend/src/core/guards/jwt-auth.guard.ts\n12. backend/src/shared/dtos/response-payload.dto.ts\n13. backend/src/shared/dtos/pagination.dto.ts\n14. backend/src/modules/ (list all module directories)\n\nReturn full file contents for each.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_1c02c2166ffeEnvE6ASRgv4xow (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere are the full contents of all 14 requested items:\n\n---\n\n### 1. `backend/src/core/base/base.entity.ts`\n\n```ts\nimport {\n    PrimaryGeneratedColumn,\n    CreateDateColumn,\n    UpdateDateColumn,\n    DeleteDateColumn,\n} from 'typeorm';\n\nexport abstract class BaseEntity {\n    @PrimaryGeneratedColumn('uuid')\n    id: string;\n\n    @CreateDateColumn({ name: 'created_at', type: 'timestamp' })\n    createdAt: Date;\n\n    @UpdateDateColumn({ name: 'updated_at', type: 'timestamp' })\n    updatedAt: Date;\n\n    @DeleteDateColumn({ name: 'deleted_at', type: 'timestamp', nullable: true })\n    deletedAt: Date | null;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `backend/src/core/base/base.repository.ts`\n\n```ts\nimport {\n    Repository,\n    FindManyOptions,\n    FindOneOptions,\n    DeepPartial,\n    FindOptionsRelations,\n    QueryDeepPartialEntity,\n} from 'typeorm';\nimport { BaseEntity } from './base.entity';\n\nexport abstract class BaseRepository<T extends BaseEntity> {\n    constructor(protected readonly repository: Repository<T>) {}\n\n    async findAll(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<T[]> {\n        return this.repository.find(options);\n    }\n\n    async findById(\n        id: string,\n        relations?: FindOptionsRelations<T>,\n    ): Promise<T | null> {\n        return this.repository.findOne({\n            where: { id } as unknown as FindOneOptions<T>['where'],\n            relations,\n        });\n    }\n\n    async findOne(options: FindOneOptions<T>): Promise<T | null> {\n        return this.repository.findOne(options);\n    }\n\n    async create(data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T> {\n        const entity = this.repository.create(data);\n        return this.repository.save(entity);\n    }\n\n    async update(id: string, data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T | null> {\n        await this.repository.update(id, data as QueryDeepPartialEntity<T>);\n        return this.findById(id);\n    }\n\n    async softDelete(id: string): Promise<void> {\n        await this.repository.softDelete(id);\n    }\n\n    async delete(id: string): Promise<void> {\n        await this.repository.delete(id);\n    }\n\n    async count(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<number> {\n        return this.repository.count(options);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. `backend/src/core/base/base.service.ts`\n\n```ts\nimport { NotFoundException } from '@nestjs/common';\nimport { FindManyOptions, DeepPartial, FindOptionsRelations } from 'typeorm';\nimport { BaseRepository } from './base.repository';\nimport { BaseEntity } from './base.entity';\n\nexport abstract class BaseService<T extends BaseEntity> {\n    constructor(\n        protected readonly repository: BaseRepository<T>,\n        protected readonly entityName: string,\n    ) {}\n\n    protected defaultRelations?: FindOptionsRelations<T>;\n\n    async findByIdOrFail(\n        id: string,\n        relations?: FindOptionsRelations<T>,\n    ): Promise<T> {\n        const entity = await this.repository.findById(\n            id,\n            relations || this.defaultRelations,\n        );\n        if (!entity) {\n            throw new NotFoundException(\n                `${this.entityName} with ID ${id} not found`,\n            );\n        }\n        return entity;\n    }\n\n    async findAll(options?: FindManyOptions<T>): Promise<T[]> {\n        return this.repository.findAll({\n            ...options,\n            relations:\n                (options?.relations as FindOptionsRelations<T>) ||\n                this.defaultRelations,\n        });\n    }\n\n    async create(data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T> {\n        return this.repository.create(data);\n    }\n\n    async update(id: string, data: DeepPartial<T>): Promise<T | null> {\n        await this.findByIdOrFail(id);\n        return this.repository.update(id, data);\n    }\n\n    async remove(id: string): Promise<void> {\n        await this.findByIdOrFail(id);\n        await this.repository.softDelete(id);\n    }\n\n    async delete(id: string): Promise<void> {\n        await this.findByIdOrFail(id);\n        await this.repository.delete(id);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. `backend/src/core/base/base.controller.ts`\n\n```ts\nimport {\n    Get,\n    Post,\n    Patch,\n    Delete,\n    Body,\n    Param,\n    Query,\n    HttpCode,\n    HttpStatus,\n    ParseUUIDPipe,\n} from '@nestjs/common';\nimport {\n    ApiOperation,\n    ApiResponse,\n    ApiParam,\n    ApiQuery,\n} from '@nestjs/swagger';\nimport { BaseService } from './base.service';\nimport { BaseEntity } from './base.entity';\nimport { DeepPartial } from 'typeorm';\n\nexport abstract class BaseController<\n    T extends BaseEntity,\n    CreateDto extends DeepPartial<T> = DeepPartial<T>,\n    UpdateDto extends DeepPartial<T> = DeepPartial<T>,\n> {\n    constructor(protected readonly service: BaseService<T>) {}\n\n    @Post()\n    @HttpCode(HttpStatus.CREATED)\n    @ApiOperation({ summary: 'Create a new resource' })\n    @ApiResponse({ status: 201, description: 'Resource created successfully' })\n    @ApiResponse({ status: 400, description: 'Bad request' })\n    async create(@Body() createDto: CreateDto): Promise<T> {\n        return this.service.create(createDto);\n    }\n\n    @Get()\n    @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n    @ApiOperation({ summary: 'Get all resources' })\n    @ApiResponse({ status: 200, description: 'Resources retrieved successfully' })\n    @ApiQuery({ name: 'page', required: false, type: Number })\n    @ApiQuery({ name: 'limit', required: false, type: Number })\n    async findAll(\n        @Query('page') page?: number,\n        @Query('limit') limit?: number,\n    ): Promise<T[]> {\n        const options =\n            page && limit ? { skip: (page - 1) * limit, take: limit } : {};\n        return this.service.findAll(options);\n    }\n\n    @Get(':id')\n    @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n    @ApiOperation({ summary: 'Get a resource by ID' })\n    @ApiParam({ name: 'id', type: String, description: 'Resource UUID' })\n    @ApiResponse({ status: 200, description: 'Resource retrieved successfully' })\n    @ApiResponse({ status: 404, description: 'Resource not found' })\n    async findOne(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string): Promise<T> {\n        return this.service.findByIdOrFail(id);\n    }\n\n    @Patch(':id')\n    @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n    @ApiOperation({ summary: 'Update a resource' })\n    @ApiParam({ name: 'id', type: String, description: 'Resource UUID' })\n    @ApiResponse({ status: 200, description: 'Resource updated successfully' })\n    @ApiResponse({ status: 404, description: 'Resource not found' })\n    async update(\n        @Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string,\n        @Body() updateDto: UpdateDto,\n    ): Promise<T | null> {\n        return this.service.update(id, updateDto);\n    }\n\n    @Delete(':id')\n    @HttpCode(HttpStatus.OK)\n    @ApiOperation({ summary: 'Delete a resource' })\n    @ApiParam({ name: 'id', type: String, description: 'Resource UUID' })\n    @ApiResponse({ status: 200, description: 'Resource deleted successfully' })\n    @ApiResponse({ status: 404, description: 'Resource not found' })\n    async remove(@Param('id', ParseUUIDPipe) id: string): Promise<void> {\n        return this.service.remove(id);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. `backend/src/core/base/index.ts`\n\n```ts\nexport { BaseEntity } from './base.entity';\nexport { BaseRepository } from './base.repository';\nexport { BaseService } from './base.service';\nexport { BaseController } from './base.controller';\n```\n\n---\n\n### 6. `backend/src/core/decorators/index.ts`\n\n```ts\nexport { Public, IS_PUBLIC_KEY } from './public.decorator';\nexport { Roles, ROLES_KEY } from './roles.decorator';\nexport { CurrentUser } from './current-user.decorator';\nexport { ApiSwagger } from './api-swagger.decorator';\nexport { ApiResponseData } from './api-response-data.decorator';\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. `backend/src/core/decorators/public.decorator.ts`\n\n```ts\nimport { SetMetadata } from '@nestjs/common';\n\nexport const IS_PUBLIC_KEY = 'isPublic';\nexport const Public = () => SetMetadata(IS_PUBLIC_KEY, true);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. `backend/src/core/decorators/roles.decorator.ts`\n\n```ts\nimport { SetMetadata } from '@nestjs/common';\n\nexport const ROLES_KEY = 'roles';\n\n/**\n * Mark a route with required roles.\n * Uses string[] to stay generic — projects can narrow to their own RoleEnum after copying.\n *\n * Usage: @Roles('admin', 'manager')\n */\nexport const Roles = (...roles: string[]) => SetMetadata(ROLES_KEY, roles);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 9. `backend/src/core/decorators/current-user.decorator.ts`\n\n```ts\nimport { createParamDecorator, ExecutionContext } from '@nestjs/common';\n\n/**\n * Extract the current authenticated user from the request.\n *\n * Usage:\n *   @CurrentUser() user: IJwtPayload          — full user object\n *   @CurrentUser('id') userId: string          — specific field\n */\nexport const CurrentUser = createParamDecorator(\n    (data: string | undefined, ctx: ExecutionContext) => {\n        const request = ctx.switchToHttp().getRequest();\n        const user = request.user;\n        return data ? user?.[data] : user;\n    },\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 10. `backend/src/core/decorators/api-swagger.decorator.ts`\n\n```ts\nimport { applyDecorators, Type } from \"@nestjs/common\";\nimport {\n  ApiOperation,\n  ApiResponse,\n  ApiBody,\n  ApiBearerAuth,\n  ApiCookieAuth,\n  ApiExtraModels,\n  ApiParam,\n  ApiQuery,\n  getSchemaPath,\n} from \"@nestjs/swagger\";\nimport { ResponsePayloadDto, ErrorDetailDto } from \"../../shared/dtos\";\nimport { ApiResponseData } from \"./api-response-data.decorator\";\n\nexport interface ErrorResponseConfig {\n  status: number;\n  description?: string;\n}\n\nexport type ApiOperationType =\n  | \"create\"\n  | \"getAll\"\n  | \"getOne\"\n  | \"update\"\n  | \"delete\"\n  | \"search\"\n  | \"count\"\n  | \"custom\";\n\nexport interface ApiSwaggerOptions {\n  /** Resource name (e.g., 'User', 'Product') */\n  resourceName: string;\n  /** Request body DTO */\n  requestDto?: Type<any>;\n  /** Response data DTO (used in ResponsePayloadDto.data) */\n  responseDto?: Type<any>;\n  /** HTTP success status code (default: 200) */\n  successStatus?: number;\n  /** If true, response data is an array */\n  isArray?: boolean;\n  /** Whether endpoint requires bearer auth (default: true) */\n  requiresAuth?: boolean;\n  /** Array of error responses to document */\n  errors?: ErrorResponseConfig[];\n  /** Operation type for auto-generating summary and common errors */\n  operation?: ApiOperationType;\n  /** Custom operation summary (overrides auto-generated) */\n  summary?: string;\n  /** ID parameter name for getOne/update/delete (default: 'id') */\n  paramName?: string;\n  /** Add pagination query params for getAll (default: false) */\n  withPagination?: boolean;\n}\n\nexport function ApiSwagger(options: ApiSwaggerOptions) {\n  const config: Required<\n    Pick<\n      ApiSwaggerOptions,\n      | \"successStatus\"\n      | \"isArray\"\n      | \"requiresAuth\"\n      | \"withPagination\"\n      | \"paramName\"\n      | \"operation\"\n    >\n  > &\n    ApiSwaggerOptions = {\n    successStatus: 200,\n    isArray: false,\n    requiresAuth: true,\n    withPagination: false,\n    paramName: \"id\",\n    operation: \"custom\",\n    ...options,\n  };\n\n  const decorators: Array<\n    ClassDecorator | MethodDecorator | PropertyDecorator\n  > = [];\n\n  decorators.push(ApiExtraModels(ResponsePayloadDto, ErrorDetailDto));\n\n  // Auto-generate summary from operation type\n  let summary = config.summary;\n  if (!summary && config.operation) {\n    const resourceLower = config.resourceName.toLowerCase();\n    switch (config.operation) {\n      case \"create\":\n        summary = `Create a new ${resourceLower}`;\n        break;\n      case \"getAll\":\n        summary = `Get all ${resourceLower}`;\n        break;\n      case \"getOne\":\n        summary = `Get ${resourceLower} by ${config.paramName}`;\n        break;\n      case \"update\":\n        summary = `Update ${resourceLower}`;\n        break;\n      case \"delete\":\n        summary = `Delete ${resourceLower}`;\n        break;\n      case \"search\":\n        summary = `Search ${resourceLower}`;\n        break;\n      case \"count\":\n        summary = `Count ${resourceLower}`;\n        break;\n      default:\n        summary = config.resourceName;\n    }\n  }\n\n  decorators.push(ApiOperation({ summary }));\n\n  // Add param decorator for single-resource operations\n  if ([\"getOne\", \"update\", \"delete\"].includes(config.operation)) {\n    decorators.push(\n      ApiParam({\n        name: config.paramName,\n        type: String,\n        format: \"uuid\",\n        description: `${config.resourceName} ${config.paramName}`,\n      }),\n    );\n  }\n\n  // Add pagination query params\n  if (config.operation === \"getAll\" && config.withPagination) {\n    decorators.push(\n      ApiQuery({ name: \"page\", required: false, type: Number, example: 1 }),\n      ApiQuery({ name: \"limit\", required: false, type: Number, example: 10 }),\n      ApiQuery({ name: \"search\", required: false, type: String }),\n      ApiQuery({\n        name: \"sortBy\",\n        required: false,\n        type: String,\n        example: \"createdAt\",\n      }),\n      ApiQuery({\n        name: \"sortOrder\",\n        required: false,\n        enum: [\"ASC\", \"DESC\"],\n        example: \"DESC\",\n      }),\n    );\n  }\n\n  // Auth decorators\n  if (config.requiresAuth) {\n    decorators.push(ApiBearerAuth());\n    // TODO: CUSTOMIZE — Match this to your AUTH_TOKEN_COOKIE_NAME env var\n    decorators.push(ApiCookieAuth(\"access_token\"));\n    decorators.push(\n      ApiResponse({\n        status: 401,\n        description: \"Unauthorized - Invalid or missing authentication token\",\n        schema: {\n          type: \"object\",\n          properties: {\n            success: { type: \"boolean\", example: false },\n            statusCode: { type: \"number\", example: 401 },\n            message: { type: \"string\", example: \"Unauthorized\" },\n            data: { type: \"null\", nullable: true, example: null },\n            error: {\n              type: \"array\",\n              items: { $ref: getSchemaPath(ErrorDetailDto) },\n            },\n          },\n        },\n      }),\n    );\n  }\n\n  if (config.requestDto) {\n    decorators.push(ApiBody({ type: config.requestDto }));\n  }\n\n  // Success response\n  if (config.responseDto) {\n    decorators.push(\n      ApiResponseData(\n        config.responseDto,\n        config.successStatus,\n        config.isArray,\n      ) as any,\n    );\n  } else {\n    decorators.push(\n      ApiResponse({\n        status: config.successStatus,\n        description: \"Successful response\",\n        schema: { $ref: getSchemaPath(ResponsePayloadDto) },\n      }),\n    );\n  }\n\n  // Auto-generate common error responses based on operation\n  const autoErrors: ErrorResponseConfig[] = [];\n  if (config.operation === \"create\") {\n    autoErrors.push(\n      { status: 400, description: \"Validation failed\" },\n      { status: 409, description: `${config.resourceName} already exists` },\n    );\n  } else if ([\"getOne\", \"update\", \"delete\"].includes(config.operation)) {\n    autoErrors.push({\n      status: 404,\n      description: `${config.resourceName} not found`,\n    });\n    if (config.operation === \"update\") {\n      autoErrors.push({ status: 400, description: \"Validation failed\" });\n    }\n  }\n\n  const allErrors = [...autoErrors, ...(config.errors || [])];\n  const uniqueErrors = Array.from(\n    new Map(allErrors.map((e) => [e.status, e])).values(),\n  );\n\n  uniqueErrors.forEach((error) => {\n    decorators.push(\n      ApiResponse({\n        status: error.status,\n        description: error.description || `Error ${error.status}`,\n      }),\n    );\n  });\n\n  return applyDecorators(...decorators);\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 11. `backend/src/core/guards/jwt-auth.guard.ts`\n\n```ts\nimport {\n    Injectable,\n    ExecutionContext,\n    UnauthorizedException,\n} from '@nestjs/common';\nimport { AuthGuard } from '@nestjs/passport';\nimport { Reflector } from '@nestjs/core';\nimport { IS_PUBLIC_KEY } from '../decorators/public.decorator';\n\n@Injectable()\nexport class JwtAuthGuard extends AuthGuard('jwt') {\n    constructor(private reflector: Reflector) {\n        super();\n    }\n\n    canActivate(context: ExecutionContext) {\n        // Check if route is marked as @Public()\n        const isPublic = this.reflector.getAllAndOverride<boolean>(\n            IS_PUBLIC_KEY,\n            [context.getHandler(), context.getClass()],\n        );\n\n        if (isPublic) {\n            return true; // Skip authentication for public routes\n        }\n\n        // Execute passport JWT strategy\n        return super.canActivate(context);\n    }\n\n    handleRequest(err: any, user: any, info: any) {\n        if (err || !user) {\n            throw err || new UnauthorizedException('Invalid or expired token');\n        }\n        return user;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 12. `backend/src/shared/dtos/response-payload.dto.ts`\n\n```ts\nimport { ApiProperty, ApiPropertyOptional } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n\nexport class ErrorDetailDto {\n    @ApiProperty({\n        example: 'email',\n        description: 'Field name related to the error (if applicable)',\n    })\n    field?: string;\n\n    @ApiProperty({\n        example: 'Invalid format',\n        description: 'Human readable reason for the error',\n    })\n    reason?: string;\n\n    @ApiPropertyOptional({\n        example: { minLength: 'Must be at least 8 characters' },\n        description: 'Constraint keys and messages (from class-validator)',\n    })\n    constraints?: Record<string, string>;\n\n    @ApiPropertyOptional({\n        example: 'INVALID_EMAIL',\n        description: 'Machine-friendly error code',\n    })\n    code?: string;\n}\n\nexport class ResponsePayloadDto<T = unknown> {\n    @ApiProperty({ example: true, description: 'Request success indicator' })\n    success: boolean;\n\n    @ApiProperty({ example: 200, description: 'HTTP status code' })\n    statusCode: number;\n\n    @ApiProperty({ example: 'Operation completed successfully' })\n    message: string;\n\n    @ApiPropertyOptional({ description: 'Response data' })\n    data?: T;\n\n    @ApiPropertyOptional({\n        description: 'Error details (only on error responses)',\n        type: [ErrorDetailDto],\n    })\n    error?: ErrorDetailDto[];\n\n    @ApiPropertyOptional({ example: '2024-11-02T10:30:00.000Z' })\n    timestamp?: string;\n\n    @ApiPropertyOptional({ example: '/api/v1/users' })\n    path?: string;\n\n    constructor(partial: Partial<ResponsePayloadDto<T>>) {\n        Object.assign(this, partial);\n        this.timestamp = this.timestamp || new Date().toISOString();\n    }\n}\n\nexport class SuccessResponseDto<T = unknown> extends ResponsePayloadDto<T> {\n    constructor(\n        data: T,\n        message: string = 'Success',\n        statusCode: number = 200,\n    ) {\n        super({\n            success: true,\n            statusCode,\n            message,\n            data,\n            timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n        });\n    }\n}\n\nexport class ErrorResponseDto extends ResponsePayloadDto {\n    constructor(\n        message: string,\n        statusCode: number = 500,\n        error?: ErrorDetailDto[],\n        path?: string,\n    ) {\n        super({\n            success: false,\n            statusCode,\n            message,\n            error,\n            path,\n            timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n        });\n    }\n}\n\nexport class PaginationMetaDto {\n    @ApiProperty({ example: 1 })\n    page: number;\n\n    @ApiProperty({ example: 10 })\n    limit: number;\n\n    @ApiProperty({ example: 100 })\n    total: number;\n\n    @ApiProperty({ example: 10 })\n    totalPages: number;\n\n    @ApiProperty({ example: true })\n    hasNextPage: boolean;\n\n    @ApiProperty({ example: false })\n    hasPreviousPage: boolean;\n\n    constructor(page: number, limit: number, total: number) {\n        this.page = page;\n        this.limit = limit;\n        this.total = total;\n        this.totalPages = Math.ceil(total / limit);\n        this.hasNextPage = page < this.totalPages;\n        this.hasPreviousPage = page > 1;\n    }\n}\n\nexport class PaginatedResponseDto<T = unknown> extends ResponsePayloadDto<T[]> {\n    @ApiProperty({ description: 'Pagination metadata' })\n    meta: PaginationMetaDto;\n\n    constructor(\n        data: T[],\n        page: number,\n        limit: number,\n        total: number,\n        message: string = 'Data retrieved successfully',\n    ) {\n        super({\n            success: true,\n            statusCode: 200,\n            message,\n            data,\n            timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n        });\n        this.meta = new PaginationMetaDto(page, limit, total);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 13. `backend/src/shared/dtos/pagination.dto.ts`\n\n```ts\nimport {\n    IsOptional,\n    IsInt,\n    Min,\n    Max,\n    IsIn,\n    IsString,\n} from 'class-validator';\nimport { Type } from 'class-transformer';\nimport { ApiPropertyOptional } from '@nestjs/swagger';\n\nexport class PaginationDto {\n    @ApiPropertyOptional({ example: 1, description: 'Page number' })\n    @IsOptional()\n    @Type(() => Number)\n    @IsInt()\n    @Min(1)\n    page?: number = 1;\n\n    @ApiPropertyOptional({ example: 10, description: 'Items per page' })\n    @IsOptional()\n    @Type(() => Number)\n    @IsInt()\n    @Min(1)\n    @Max(100)\n    limit?: number = 10;\n\n    @ApiPropertyOptional({ example: 'createdAt', description: 'Sort by field' })\n    @IsOptional()\n    @IsString()\n    sortBy?: string;\n\n    @ApiPropertyOptional({ enum: ['ASC', 'DESC'], example: 'DESC' })\n    @IsOptional()\n    @IsIn(['ASC', 'DESC'])\n    sortOrder?: 'ASC' | 'DESC' = 'DESC';\n\n    @ApiPropertyOptional({ description: 'Search query' })\n    @IsOptional()\n    @IsString()\n    search?: string;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 14. `backend/src/modules/` -- Module Directories\n\nThe following 5 module directories exist under `backend/src/modules/`:\n\n| Directory | Full Path |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| `auth/` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/modules/auth/` |\n| `favorites/` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/modules/favorites/` |\n| `inquiries/` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/modules/inquiries/` |\n| `properties/` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/modules/properties/` |\n| `users/` | `/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/backend/src/modules/users/` |\n</task_result>","metad